title: italian zucchini
directions: In a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole, layer 1/3 of the zucchini, onion and tomatoes.
Squeeze 1 lemon quarter over all.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon Italian seasoning and 1/4 teaspoon red pepper flakes.
Repeat layers.
Dot with butter.
Squeeze remaining lemon over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients, then fold in topping.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; chill. Drain cherries on paper towels. Pack chilled mixture around cherries and roll into a ball. Freeze cherries. Melt chocolate and paraffin together in a double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate. If mixture gets too soft to handle, just chill again, then dip.

title: pepper relish
directions: Wash, trim and quarter peppers and onions.
Put vegetables through a food grinder, using coarse blade; drain, discarding liquid.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in a saucepan; heat to boiling.
Add vegetables; simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Continue simmering while quickly packing vegetables into hot sterilized jars.
Leave 1/2-inch headspace.
Make sure vinegar solution covers vegetables.
Release air bubbles; clean tops and threads of jar.
Tighten lids on jars.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 pints.

title: easy low-fat carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bundt pan makes a pretty cake, but you can use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spray with a nonstick vegetable spray.

title: heavenly cranberry sauce
directions: Wash cranberries and drain well.
Place in shallow baking dish and cover with chopped walnuts, sugar, lemon juice and grated lemon rind and orange marmalade.
Cover tightly and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: cheese dip
directions: *If you use Russian (bought) dressing, add some dry minced onions.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bacon cheddar puffs
directions: Bring milk and margarine to a boil over medium heat.
Add flour, all at once, stirring constantly, until the mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat; add eggs, one at a time, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
(These freeze well.)

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries, orange pulp and apples through food grinder or use food processor.
Add sugar and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
This relish may be frozen.
Makes about 4 pints.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with 3 cups milk according to directions. Add condensed milk and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas.
Spread pudding mixture over wafers and bananas.
Repeat until all is used, ending with pudding mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: tina's spiced tea
directions: Mix and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
May use a crock-pot.

title: orange cream
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add ice cream and stir until completely melted.
Add oranges, nuts and marshmallows and mix well.
Pour into dish.
Chill until firm.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cream the sugar, flour and salt with butter.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Blend in milk and raisins.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sherry's meatballs
directions: Make small balls and place in pan to bake in oven.

title: simple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk in a bowl.
Batter will be thin. Grease a 9-inch cake pan and flour it lightly.
Pour batter into cake pan.
Drain fruit and spoon fruit on top of mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
It will be brown on top.

title: grandma's bread and butter pickles
directions: Do not peel cucumbers. Slice; add onions, peppers and whole garlic. Add salt; let stand for 3 hours. Drain. Combine sugar, vinegar, turmeric and celery seed and pour over pickle mixture. Heat just to a boil; then seal in pint jars. Yields 8 pints.

title: bean n' bacon salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients; toss lightly.
Cover and chill. Mix together eggs, mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar and salt.
Just before serving, drain the bean mixture and toss with bacon.
Top with egg mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve on top of crisp greens.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Combine first six ingredients and saute with hamburger.
Drain. Add tomato sauce and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut up scallions and blend with cream cheese and sour cream.
Cook noodles according to package.
In slightly greased casserole dish, place 1/3 noodles, 1/2 scallion mixture and 1/3 meat sauce, three times (as if lasagna).
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry-pineapple pie
directions: Melt marshmallows and pineapple and cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and strawberries.
Put in baked pie shell.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: sheet cookies
directions: Beat margarine, eggs and sugar well (thick dough).
Add flour and vanilla.
Put batter on large cookie sheet (with sides) to a depth of 1/4 to 1/2-inch.
Divide by scoring 3 x 3-inch and fill each division with filling (use entire can).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: stuffed bread dip
directions: Combine all ingredients several hours before serving.
Serve in hollowed out loaf bread (pound loaf) with cubed bread and crackers to dip.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Mix well, then chill.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: yankee doodle macaroni
directions: Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms until onion is yellow in
3 tablespoons of fat.
Add ground beef and cook until brown.
Add and cook slowly the tomatoes, minced parsley, salt and pepper for about 45 minutes.
Pour over hot, drained, boiled macaroni. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken pot pie(so easy, so good)
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients together except milk and Bisquick and pour over margarine.
Mix milk and Bisquick and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Separate into pieces, lining a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, chicken broth and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Mix with mixer until smooth the flour, buttermilk and margarine.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan crunch pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy; slowly add sugar and baking powder.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in nuts, graham crackers and vanilla.
Pour into well-buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef and onions over medium heat.
Drain on paper towels.
Return to soup pot and add next 8 ingredients (tomatoes, water, bouillon, salt, pepper, bay leaf, celery and Worcestershire sauce).
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add vegetables, noodles and thyme.
Bring to a boil, simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and zucchini. Add flour and the rest of the ingredients. Grease 2 bread pans and flour them. Divide batter into pans and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: nutmeg logs
directions: Cream butter with flavorings; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in egg.
Add flour, nutmeg and salt, mixing well.
Shape pieces of dough on sugared board into long rolls 1/2-inch in diameter.
Cut into 2-inch lengths and put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Just lightly browned on bottoms.
Cool.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll and cut in strips or rounds.
Does very well to use a cookie press.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook the peas in water with a little salt and sugar.
Drain. Chop the celery, onion and green pepper very fine and grate the carrot.
Slice mushrooms, if they're small, or chop them if they're larger.
Combine all the ingredients and season well with salt and pepper.
Serve with cold meat.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Mix the next 6 ingredients.
After creaming together, add the oats mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven, or until cake pulls away from pan.
(Use an 8 x 10 x 3-inch pan.) While cake is baking, fix topping.

title: easy hot peas
directions: Heat soup and add cheese; stir until melted.
Add peas and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until peas are hot.

title: pam's favorite chicken
directions: Set out all ingredients, so you don't have to get into packages or the refrigerator with "chicken hands".

title: carrot pineapple salad(good low-fat recipe)
directions: Dissolve orange jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add juice of pineapple and 1 cup carrots.
Chill until firm.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup hot water; let cool.
Add yogurt or buttermilk. Pour over other mixture and chill.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and egg. Stir in cocoa.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Drop onto cookie sheets by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
After cookies cool, can be topped with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook pork, beef and chicken until tender; cool.
Cut up in very small pieces, add tomatoes, potatoes, onions and peas; simmer covered for about 1/2 hour.
Add corn and seasonings while hot.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown ground beef in 3 tablespoons of butter.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onions and green peppers.
Spread half of cooked noodles in a greased casserole.
Cover with entire cheese mixture.
Add remaining noodles.
Pour 2 tablespoons melted butter over noodles.
Put meat sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake(out of this world cake)
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix together 2 teaspoons of baking powder, graham crackers (crushed) and vanilla.
Mix with the first mixture.
Add nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in 3 layer pans.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt margarine; add flour.
Cook 5 minutes slowly.
Heat milk; add slowly to margarine and flour.
Stir constantly.
Add cheese; cook slowly.

title: potato soup
directions: In large sauce pan add 5 cups water and bouillon cubes.
After frying bacon, remove bacon grease.
Use butter in frying pan. Saute all vegetables EXCEPT potatoes in frying pan.
Cook potatoes in water and bouillon cubes.
Add sauteed vegetables until potatoes are done.
During the last 15 minutes, add the evaporated milk.

title: gail's enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Set aside.
Chop onions, if desired, and grate cheese.
Place cooking oil in skillet enough to cover corn tortillas and get hot.
Drop corn tortillas into hot grease until soft.
(It only takes a few seconds.)
Remove tortillas from grease and drain.
Place tortillas in a baking pan and fill with beef, onion and cheese mixture.
Roll tortillas up. Continue placing tortillas in grease, stuffing and rolling until all of beef is gone.
Open cans of El Paso sauce and pour over enchiladas.
Cover completely.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese and onions.
Place in oven at 350° and bake for 15 to 30 minutes or until the cheese melts.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Add berries and pineapple.
Let set.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Pour over Cool Whip mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Freeze.
Before serving, break into slush.

title: taco dip
directions: Saute meat and 1/4 cup onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in catsup, chili powder, salt and beans.
Mix well.
Spoon into ungreased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining 1/3 cup onion, cheese and olives on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes about four cups.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mushrooms florentine
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well and squeeze excess liquid.
Spoon spinach evenly into bottom of shallow casserole.
Sprinkle with salt, chopped onion and 2 tablespoons melted butter and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chewy cheese cake
directions: Mix together.
Press in pan sprayed with Pam.

title: chex school fuel
directions: Microwave brown sugar, margarine and corn syrup in large microwavable bowl uncovered on High 1 to 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute, until margarine is melted.
Stir in baking soda until dissolved.
Stir in cereals. Microwave on High 3 minutes stirring every minute. Spread on wax paper. Cool 10 minutes; break into bite-size pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Stir together the sauerkraut, celery, pepper and onion.
Mix together the sugar, oil and vinegar.
Combine with the sauerkraut mixture; marinate for 24 hours before serving.

title: white strawberry sangria
directions: In a 2-quart pitcher, stir together wine, Schnapps and sugar until sugar dissolves. Add strawberries and chill 1 to 4 hours. Serve over ice. Makes 5 to 6 servings (8 ounces each). Delicious!

title: raisin bran cookies(weight watchers only)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Fold in grated apple.
Drop from spoon onto cookie sheet that has been sprayed with nonstick agent.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 serving for breakfast.

title: oven-baked potatoes
directions: Place dry soup mix and oil into a large Ziploc bag. Knead until soup mix is moistened with oil. Add potatoes. Shake well until potato cubes are well coated. Spray a 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Pour potatoes into pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cheesy hash browns 'n' ham
directions: Spread 1 teaspoon margarine on each side of each frozen hash brown patty.
Place patties on ungreased cookie sheet.
Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat for 11 to 13 minutes or until brown.
Turn patties over; broil 4 to 6 minutes or until brown.
Place ham slice on each hash brown patty; broil for 1 to 2 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle cheese and parsley over ham.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Coarsely shred 3 to 4 cups cabbage into casserole dish.
Saute onion in margarine, then add ground beef and cook with onion. Don't brown. Spoon half of this over cabbage.
Repeat with cabbage and beef. Spread condensed tomato soup over top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix with other ingredients.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on pan.
Bake at 375°. Ice with powdered sugar icing.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner. Stir in soup and milk. Gently stir in the tuna.
Heat all the ingredients to serving temperature.

title: homemade gatorade
directions: Combine sugar and salt.
Add hot water and mix.
Add orange juice and mix.
Add cold water and lemon juice; mix.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Mix cake mix
(except 3/4 cup), butter and egg as crust and put in a
x
13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Mix other ingredients
and
pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until pie-like.

title: cranberry cake with butter sauce
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture, mixing with the milk.
Add cranberries (fresh or frozen).
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with sauce.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add 1/4 cup milk; stir until well mixed.
Add egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar and 2 cups milk.
Cook, stirring, until thick.
Remove from heat. Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
(This pie is foolproof and delicious.) Top with meringue.

title: crisp
directions: Mix flour, oats, brown sugar and softened butter until it crumbles.
Put 1/2 of crumbs in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix drained peaches or apples with sugar and cinnamon.
Put over crumbs and cover with rest of crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and 1 teaspoon water in 8-inch round microwave dish.
Cook, uncovered, on 70% power for 2 minutes or until butter melts.
Stir mixture and spread over bottom of pan. Sprinkle nuts over top.
Place biscuits on top of mixture.
Bake, uncovered, on 70% powder for 4 to 5 minutes or until biscuits are firm and no longer doughy.
Let stand about 2 minutes.
Invert onto a flat serving plate.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop about 1 teaspoon at a time in hot fat. Serve hot.

title: brenda's taco salad
directions: Mix everything together well.
This is better the day after you make it.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Start a 25 briquette fire.
While it is burning down to a cooking glow, prepare the main course.
Use a 12-inch glass baking dish, about 2-inches deep.
Take 1 1/2 pounds of pork sausage and press into the dish, as if you were making a pie crust.
Avoid thin spots in the sausage.
Break 8 eggs and stir lightly to break yolks.
Pour on top of sausage, taking care not to overfill.
Add hickory wood to the coals and place the dish on the grill.
Close hood.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, oil, sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and cream well.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press down lightly with glass dipped in water, then sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until light brown around edges.

title: spinach-beef-rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion and mushrooms and saute 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup of each cheese and rest of ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° to heat through, 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Melt.
Do not overbake.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar; slowly add cornstarch and flour.
Mix well.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add peanut butter and pour into 9 inch baked pie shell.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Cool before cutting.

title: busy day stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a large covered pan (do not brown meat).
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: dixie's crumbles
directions: Put peanut butter, chocolate morsels in a large microwave-safe bowl and melt in microwave, stirring well.
Add box of Crispix gradually until all is coated.
Put box of powdered sugar in
a large bag.
Add peanut butter mixture and shake until all is coated with the sugar.
Separate if necessary.

title: porky pines
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Make into meatballs.
Place in ungreased baking pan.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes.
Bake at 350°.

title: yogurt sauce
directions: In a small bowl, combine all sauce ingredients.
Blend well. Chill.
Great on salads. Scrumptious on a baked potato.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix ingredients and bake until it is done.
Can be eaten hot or cold.
More delicious topped with whipped cream.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole.
This can be done the day before and refrigerated.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef n' tater casserole
directions: Crumble meat in a 2-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave oven on full power for 3 to 4 minutes or until beef is no longer pink. Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain.
Top with tater tots and onion.
Mix soups together and pour over tater tots.
Bake in microwave oven on full power for 12 to 14 minutes or until heated through, and temperature of 150 degrees is reached.

title: grilled cabbage
directions: Take cabbage and cut into chunks.
Place chunks in aluminum foil.
Layer with butter, salt and pepper to your taste.
Sprinkle with a small amount of garlic.
Place strips of bacon on top. Close foil.
Place on grill at low temperature for about an hour, checking periodically.
Open foil for about the last 15 minutes. Cook to your desire.
Generally when bacon is done, cabbage is done.
Can be done on regular charcoal grill, but works best on gas grill.
Be sure to keep temperature low and cook slow.

title: chicken in a bag(serves 3 to 4)
directions: Truss chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients and rub with mixture.
Put in a paper log and bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Put chicken on a jelly roll pan to catch drippings.
Remove the bag the last 30 minutes to brown.
For chickens 3 pounds or less, bake for 2 hours.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In large bowl combine cauliflower, lettuce, bacon and onion. Spread mayonnaise over the top.
Sprinkle cheese and sugar over the top.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.
Toss just before serving.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Add Mexicorn and mushroom soup to the rice mixture. Put into a greased casserole dish. Top with cheese and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add garlic powder, parsley, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: beef rouladen
directions: Have butcher slice roast into 6 (1/4-inch thick) slices. Sprinkle beef with salt and pepper; set aside.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in a large Dutch oven.
Add bread crumbs and garlic; brown 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in eggs, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Spoon 1/3 cup bread crumb mixture on each beef slice.
Roll each piece in jelly roll fashion; secure with wooden picks.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add Vegeburger, chili, tomato sauce, catsup and salt.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Put burger mix into flat casserole dish, alternating with cubed cheese and Fritos, ending with Fritos.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: country fried cube steaks with gravy
directions: Combine flour, corn meal, salt and pepper in a shallow dish. Beat eggs and water together.
Put 1 tablespoon flour in plastic food storage bag.
Add the cube steak; shake to coat lightly.
Dip steaks in egg-water mixture, then in corn meal to coat.
Fry steaks in oil until tender.

title: lemon lust
directions: To make crust, blend flour, oleo and nuts until it forms a soft dough.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mundel kruntz
directions: Mix together.
Roll out thin.
Cut with end of glass or cookie cutters.
Slightly beat egg whites.
Use pastry brush and spread on top.
Sprinkle nuts or colored sugars on immediately, if desired. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: magic rainbow cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine. Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: date balls
directions: Heat butter, dates and brown sugar until melted.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll in small balls.
Roll balls in confectioners sugar.

title: sunny glazed pears
directions: Drain pears and reserve 2 tablespoons syrup.
Combine pear syrup with orange marmalade, lemon juice and mustard.
Place pear halves, cut side up on baking dish.
Brush cut surface and fill center of pears with orange marmalade glaze.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until pears are heated thoroughly.
Remaining sauce may be poured in baking dish.

title: sugar-free applesauce cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Combine eggs, oil and sweetener in separate bowl and mix well.
Add soda to applesauce and stir. Mix flour mixture alternately with applesauce into egg mixture. Bake in buttered loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese corn fritters
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Add flour and baking powder.
Stir in cheese, bacon bits and corn.
Cook the same as pancakes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Melt cheese in microwave.
Add refried beans, beef and onion mixture and salsa.
Keep warm in crock-pot.
Serve with taco chips.

title: sugar-free mile high pineapple pie
directions: Mix pineapple with juice in large bowl with pudding mix (dry). When mixed, add sour cream, mixing well.
Fold 2/3 of Cool Whip into pineapple mixture.
Put in crust and top with rest of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: carrot cake with coconut and pineapple
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs; add oil, buttermilk sugar and vanilla.
Mix together.
Add to dry ingredients, blending well.
Mix in drained pineapple, carrots, coconut and nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool before frosting.

title: bride's punch
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Add Kool-Aid, sugar, cold water and juice.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, add 7-Up and sherbet ice cream.
This punch makes a pink color.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, green pepper, spices, rice and ketchup in bowl.
Make into balls.
Brown in skillet.
Pour off grease. Add tomato soup mixed well with 1/2 can water.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: pineapple hawaiian cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside. Mix remaining ingredients. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and cook noodles until desired tenderness.
Mix soup and 1/2 cheese with meat.
Add noodles.
Pour in baking dish and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: vickie's combination salad
directions: First, peel the cucumbers; add salt and a little vinegar.
Let sit.
Cut tomatoes in large chunks.
Add boiled eggs (sliced), the diced onions and the Miracle Whip dressing.
Stir and put in refrigerator for a few hours.
It makes its own juice; so good you'll want to drink it.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix
cornmeal,	flour,	salt,
peppers	and sugar.
Add milk, then stir in eggs;	blend well.
Add onions and pimento. Drop in hot deep fat.

title: 2 minute fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in pan.
Cool and cut.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix with pudding according to the directions on the box with one exception, put yolks only into the cake mixture. Save the three egg whites for the 7 Minute Icing.

title: parmesan catfish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a shallow dish, combine the flour, Parmesan cheese, cornmeal, paprika, salt and pepper; set aside.
In another shallow dish, beat egg white and milk.
Dip fillets in milk mixture, then in flour mixture.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: cauliflower and corn casserole
directions: Cut up cauliflower; cook in salt water until tender.
Drain and put into square baking dish.
Add corn and toss.
Mix soup with milk and pour over cauliflower mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: grandma helen's stuffed peppers
directions: To soup, add 1 can water and sugar to taste.
Stir until smooth.
Bring to boil.
Core out seeds of peppers; wash and set aside.
Parboil rice for 10 minutes.
Rinse and strain.
Add to meat, onion, garlic, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stuff into peppers.
Place peppers into tomato soup and when it starts to boil again, lower heat and let slowly boil for 1 hour.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve as dip with Doritos. (Onions, vinegar and seasoning can be adjusted to taste.)

title: black or white peanut clusters(microwave)
directions: Place chocolate or white morsels in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-proof dish and microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until melted.
Add peanut butter and shortening.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until mixture is smooth and creamy. Blend well, stirring in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Chill until set.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 dozen clusters.

title: potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, cream cheese, margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on high until lumps are gone.
Makes 3 to 4 pies. Bake at 300° to 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: uncle mike's chili
directions: Cook onions in water for 4 minutes. Mince ground beef and add to onions and water in Dutch oven. Add chili beans, chili powder and tomato sauce. Mix thoroughly on high until boiling; reduce temperature to low and stir until satisfied chili will not stick to
pan. Serve with rice, cornbread, hot dogs or hamburgers. If you have some leftover, freeze and use for a later date.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with juice.
Lastly, add nuts and cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a bread pan.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend together Crisco, sugars and egg.
Add peanut butter and stir in flour.
Form the dough into balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Press with a fork. Bake at 350° until done.

title: spaghetti and meatballs, paolo
directions: Heat oil, lightly browning garlic.
Add tomato paste, cooking until oil turns red. Then add sauce and other seasonings.
Simmer 4 hours.

title: ma neeley's molasses cookies
directions: Cream together first 7 ingredients.
Blend in molasses.
Beat in egg.
Add flour and coffee alternately.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done; remove bones and cut into small pieces.
In a 8 x 8-inch baking dish, combine chicken, sour cream and soup.
Melt margarine in microwave oven and crumble crackers in the margarine.
Be sure crackers are well coated with margarine. Sprinkle on top of chicken mixture and bake at 325° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: gran's gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together butter and brown sugar. Beat in eggs.
Combine remaining dry ingredients.
Combine vanilla with milk and stir into batter alternately with dry ingredients. Pour into greased 9-inch square pan and bake for 1 hour or until middle tests done.
May be served plain or with vanilla ice cream or lemon sauce.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Divide popcorn between 2 ungreased rectangular pans, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Heat brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt to simmering over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour over popcorn; stir until well coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Place one layer of balls so they barely touch in a well-greased 9-inch tube pan (angel food pan).
Sprinkle with a few raisins.
Add another layer of balls and sprinkle with more raisins, pressing them in slightly.
A few candied cherries can be used for looks.
Let rise for 45 minutes.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Loosen from pan.
Invert pan so butter-sugar mixture runs down over the cake.
To serve, break apart with 2 forks.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Shred cheese.
Toss with flour; mix flour in.
Rub bottom of skillet with cut clove of garlic.
Put wine in pan and heat until bubbling.
Add lemon juice and gradually add cheese.
Stir and cook until cheese is melted (low heat).
Add brandy and seasonings.
Regulate heat to low setting.

title: christmas crunch salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower, green pepper and onion into very small pieces and store in sealed plastic container at least 6 hours.
These vegetables will get very crispy.

title: tommie's chinese candy
directions: Melt butterscotch in double boiler and then add Chinese noodles.
Drop by spoonfuls on a waxed cookie sheet.
Cool and serve.

title: white christmas pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Mix together in saucepan 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt. Stir in milk gradually.
Cook over low heat, stirring until it boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in softened gelatin.
Cool.
When partially set, beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Blend in flavoring.
Gently fold in cream, whipped stiff.
Carefully fold this mixture into a meringue made of egg whites, cream of tartar and 1/2 cup sugar. Lastly fold in coconut.
Pile into pie shell.
Sprinkle with additional coconut and chill set, about 2 hours.

title: louisiana pecan pie
directions: Melt butter and cool.
Beat eggs with sugar and salt.
Beat well and add Karo.
Add vanilla to butter mixture and stir pecans in last.
Put in a pastry shell and cook for 40 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: quick garden cheese soup
directions: In large kettle or Dutch oven, cook celery and onions in margarine until tender; stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add water, then bouillon, pepper and veggies; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts and soup is hot.
(Do not let it come to a boil.)

title: red rice
directions: Saute onions and pepper in bacon grease.
Pour into casserole dish; add remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Cover tightly and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pink panther salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain and rinse with cold water; drain again.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt, sugar and mustard.
Then combine other ingredients.
Chill.
Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and cocoa until fluffy.
Add Cool Whip; blend well.
Spoon into pie crust.
Top with crushed peanuts, if desired.

title: jason's favorite baked chicken
directions: In a shallow dish, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Set aside.
Rinse chicken, pat dry with paper towels. Brush chicken with the melted butter or margarine.
If desired, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into crumb mixture. Bake, uncovered, in a 425° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until tender and no longer pink.

title: quick goodies
directions: Melt chocolate chips with peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Cool until firm.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna, package of Kraft dinner (prepared according to instructions) and soup.
Place half in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Add remaining mixture.
Top with potato chips. Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: salvation army donuts
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add butter or oleo to milk. Put 1 cup flour, the baking powder, nutmeg and cinnamon together and mix into milk mixture.
Add enough flour so batter can be rolled out on a board.
Cut into donut shape.
Fry in hot Crisco (about 2 pounds).
Fry to a golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper.
(I always put a piece of raw potato in the Crisco.)

title: strawberry pineapple dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Whip together, then fold in Jell-O mixture a little at a time.
Then mix thoroughly. Refrigerate.

title: overnight slaw
directions: This is the recipe used for the Turkey Biscuit Dinner.

title: southern style biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda; cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in buttermilk until dough leaves side of bowl and rounds up onto a ball.
(If dough is dry, stir in 1 or 2 tablespoons additional buttermilk.)
Turn onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly until smooth, about 10 times.
Roll or pat dough 3/4 inch thick; cut with 2 1/2 inch biscuit cutter.
Place on cookie sheet (about 1 inch apart for crusty sides, touching for soft sides). Brush tops with melted margarine or butter.
Bake until golden brown 12 to 15 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 6 large biscuits.
Serve warm with butter and honey, sure to melt in your mouth.

title: great quiche
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Sprinkle into pie shell the broccoli, cheese, bacon, onion and bell pepper.
Blend together the whipping cream, milk and eggs.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: quail or dove
directions: Scald
and
clean
quail
or dove.
Do not skin.
Split quail or	dove down back and flatten out.
Place cut side next to pan. Use
a
batter
made from beaten eggs and milk.
Salt and pepper to	taste
and
roll
in
flour.
Cook to a golden brown;
turn heat down and simmer until tender.	Use drippings to make gravy. Goes well with biscuits and mashed potatoes.

title: wrapped herb chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken on a large sheet of foil. Top each piece with 1 tablespoon herbs, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, 1 teaspoon onion powder, 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon parsley.
Fold foil tightly around the chicken with double folds on each edge.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 3 to 6 people.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Put half the Cool Whip with prepared pudding.
Place one layer of graham cracker crumbs in pan.
Then alternate pie filling and pudding mixture until you have used it all.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: dried beef pinwheels
directions: Blend	 cream
cheese,
onion,
horseradish
and Worcestershire sauce until of spreading consistency.
Carefully separate
slices
of
beef	and
lay
out
each slice, slightly overlapping,
about five across on a clean dish towel.
Do this for about 3 rows,
all
slightly
overlapping
until you have a rectangle of meat.	Spread	with cheese mixture.
Roll as for a jelly roll, using the dish	towel
to help bring up all meat at the beginning of the
roll.
Press	along with fingers and roll until completed.
When cold, use fingers to form a better roll. Just before serving, slice into 1 inch slices.

title: spritz butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter in large mixer bowl.
Add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and extracts. Gradually blend in flour, almonds and salt.
Using pastry bag and large star tip, pipe dough into rosettes or stars about 1 3/4-inches in diameter onto unbuttered cookie sheets.
Decorate with cherries, sprinkles or dragees, if desired.
Bake 10 to 20 minutes or until pale golden.
Remove from cookie sheets; cool completely on wire racks.
Yields about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: baked chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken inside and out with seasonings.
Place chicken on rack in roaster with lid.
Place water in bottom. Bake, covered, at 500° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour, sugar, brown sugar and butter.
Stir walnuts and chips in.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, buttermilk, butter, vanilla and coconut last. Pour into greased pie dish. Bake at 350° for 25 - 30 minutes.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Combine potatoes with 4 cups water; bring to boiling.
Cook, covered, about 15 minutes, until nearly tender.
Drain.
Stir sauce mix from potato mix, milk, vegetables and chicken together. Stir into potatoes.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and cook 5 to 8 minutes until slightly thickened.

title: toffee heath squares
directions: Sprinkle nuts over bottom of buttered 8 inch square dish. Put brown sugar, butter and water in 1 1/2 qt. casserole. Microwave on high for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes until thick. Stir well, quickly spread over chopped nuts. Sprinkle chocolate over toffee. Cover dish so heat melts chocolate. Let stand 5 minutes. Spread chocolate evenly over top. Refrigerate to set. Turn out of dish and break pieces to serve.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine crumbs, oleo, peanut butter and sugar.
Work together until smooth.
Press mixture into a square buttered pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over mixture.
Let set, then cut into squares.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to
300°.	Reserve
1 cup of dry cake mix. In large mixing
bowl,
combine
remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil. Mixture
will
be
crumbly.
Press	crust mixture evenly into bottom and 3/4 way	up
the
sides	of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In
same bowl, blend cream cheese and sugar.	Add 3 eggs and reserved
cake
mix;
beat
for 1 minute at medium speed.	At low speed,
slowly add milk and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Pour into crust.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: Put everything in the blender and blend at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into 4 individual ramekins.
Chill for 8 hours or overnight.

title: scallops with onions and green peppers
directions: Rinse scallops thoroughly.
Heat butter in skillet.
Stir in curry powder and saute for a minute or so.
Coat scallops with pinch of salt and pepper.
Add to skillet and saute, stirring for about 5 minutes until cooked through.
Rinse and chop up green peppers and onions.
Saute in skillet until tender.
Return scallops to skillet and add cream.
Heat slowly for about 2 minutes.
Remove.
Sprinkle chopped parsley and chives over scallops and serve alone or over steamed noodles.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together peanut butter and sugar until crumbly; put into crust bottom (but save enough to sprinkle on top later).

title: argentina stew
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven combine ribs, water, salt and pepper. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add chicken, cover and simmer 25 minutes more.
Add carrots, onions, tomatoes, potatoes, cabbage, squash or pumpkin, green pepper, parsley and garlic, cover and simmer 20 minutes more or until vegetables are tender.
Spoon off fat or cool slightly, refrigerate several hours or overnight and lift fat from surface. Return mixture to heat.
Bring to boiling.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove meat and vegetables from Dutch oven; arrange on platter.
Garnish with additional parsley, if desired. Serve with bowls of broth.
Makes 6 servings.

title: enchiladas
directions: Chicken or beef must be cooked all day in crock-pot and then remove all fat and bones.
Pull apart meat into shreds.
Add 1 teaspoon of chili powder to meat and mix thoroughly.
Heat up enough oil in a frying pan and fry each tortilla on each side for about 10 seconds.
Drain on paper towels.
You will have to add more oil as you go.
Pour a thin layer of your enchilada sauce into a 9 x 12 baking dish.
Place approximately 2 tablespoons of chicken on the edge of tortilla and then put cheese on top of meat and roll up tortilla.
Place in baking dish.
Do this until all tortillas are rolled up.
Pour the rest of the enchilada sauce over the rolled tortillas, then top with cheese, onions, olives and green chiles.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix all the above together and place between two pie crusts and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and finish baking for 30 minutes.
Make 1 (10-inch) pie.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Salt and pepper ribs as desired.
Brown in baking pan in hot oven.
Cover with foil; bake until tender.
Drain off excess grease.
Cover with barbecue sauce.
Heat through, about 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: gyoza
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together;
place 1/2 teaspoon of the mixture
in
each
square
of won ton.
Dampen 2 opposite corners of	the
won
ton with a little water; fold to form a triangle. Fold
the
narrow ends together;
press tightly. Fry in hot oil until light brown.	Drain and serve hot.

title: chili sauce
directions: Mix altogether and cook until quite thick, stirring occasionally.
Pour in hot jars and seal.

title: frozen orange mist
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; stir until sugar dissolves. Gradually add to nonfat dry milk, stirring constantly.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish.
Freeze until firm.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until stiff.
Roll mixture into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Good to freeze unbaked.

title: golden brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Combine dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine margarine, sugars and vanilla. Beat until creamy. Add eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; stir well. Fold in chocolate chips.
Turn into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: mr. t's pasta sauce
directions: In a heavy Dutch oven, saute onions in oil until tender; then add garlic and cook a few minutes longer. Add tomatoes, blend well and cook a few minutes. Add tomato paste and a can of water to blend with ingredients.
Add tomato sauce and all other ingredients except sausage.
Add enough water to correct consistency. Add sausage and simmer for 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Serve over vermicelli (very thin spaghetti) with hot crusty French bread and tossed green salad.

title: angel hair with broccoli
directions: Cut broccoli into florets.
Peel and chop the stems into small pieces.
Cook broccoli in
boiling water for about 3 to 4 minutes until tender-crisp.
Drain and place in cool water; drain.
In saucepan, heat oil and 3 tablespoons butter over medium heat.
In a large saute pan, melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter and saute scallions and garlic for 2 minutes. Add wine and cook for 5 minutes. Add melted butter and oil, then blanched broccoli.
Heat thoroughly.
Put angel hair in serving dish and toss with broccoli mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and serve at once.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll in small balls.
Roll in
sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.

title: peach sauce
directions: Drain peaches well; cut into pieces.
Whip cream until slightly thickened; beat in egg yolk.
Drizzle in honey; continue beating until thick and creamy.
Fold in peaches and extract. Chill.
Stir well before serving.
Yields 1 quart.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pack lightly into prepared bird just before roasting.
For 3 1/2 to 4 pound bird.
Or pour into greased pan and bake for about 1 hour at 300°.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Precook whole cauliflower; drain.
Place in ungreased shallow baking pan.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard.
Spread over top. Sprinkle with shredded cheese, then onion rings.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and bake enough potatoes for 1/2 per serving.
Let cool to touch.
Cut in half and scoop out, leaving 1/4-inch sides and bottom.
Put into large bowl.
Mash potatoes with milk and melted butter to make piping consistency.
Make small box instant mashed potatoes and put into first bowl.
Add large can Parmesan cheese and 2 tablespoons garlic; mix well.
Put into large piping bag with serrated tip and fill each skin with mound.
Sprinkle paprika over top.
You may refrigerate or freeze for future use.
Bake thawed potatoes at 350° until tops start to brown.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flours and salt. Add this to the sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and lemon juice; mix well. Pour into tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cut up chicken.
Put in greased casserole.
Melt cream cheese and soup together.
Put over chicken.
Cover with cracker crumbs and poppy seed.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: miniature meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
With wet hands, shape the mixture into 40 small meatballs, using about a teaspoon for each.
Place in two 9 x 13-inch pans.
All this may be done ahead of time.
About 30 minutes before serving, brown the meat balls in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove all excess grease.

title: harvest ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water and vinegar.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in vegetables and pour into 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold. Garnish with salad greens.
Yields 8 servings.

title: coconut pies
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in each pie plate.

title: fresh strawberry milk shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend until creamy.
Drink and enjoy!

title: pecan pie
directions: Prepare 2 pie shells.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, then add sugar.	Melt butter and add to mix.
Add Karo syrup, salt and pecans.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake approximately 55 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients to soft-ball stage, then add peanut butter.
Stir until creamy.
Pour into a buttered pan to cool.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.
Use 3 heaping teaspoonfuls for each cup.
Add hot water to fill the cup.

title: chicken salad party tray
directions: Place chicken salad in mold.
When it has molded, place on serving tray and place crackers around salad.
Serves 40 people.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Add egg mixture to butter and sugar mixture.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 350°.
Turn oven to 300° and bake until center no longer shakes (30 to 40 minutes usually).

title: lemon buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together in a large mixing bowl until light and lemon colored.
Beat in flour, buttermilk, butter, lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° in preheated oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until firm in center.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix together asparagus, peas, beans, pimento and eggs.
Pour in sprayed casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle onion rings on top and bake 5 more minutes.
Yield: About 8 servings.
This can easily be doubled.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Mix all together and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: crab salad
directions: Chop crab.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Serve on a croissant or bread. Serves approximately 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks and beat in.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mulled wine cider
directions: Place mull and wine in large saucepan.
Simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 (4 ounce) servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in lard until particles are size of peas.
Beat egg; blend in vinegar and cold water.
Sprinkle over flour mixture, a tablespoon at a time, tossing with fork to mix.
Gather dough together with fingers so it cleans the bowl. Chill before rolling (even better after it has been frozen).
Makes two 9-inch 2-crust pies and one 9-inch pie shell.

title: fruit tarts
directions: Use a variety or one kind of fruit; your choice.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Add onions.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Drain water.
Cover with milk.
Add margarine; bring to boil.
Mix cornstarch with a little water.
Add to mixture until you feel it thicken.
Simmer and stir for 5 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: spring rolls
directions: Cook ground beef in large pan. Add to the cooked meat bean sprouts, green onions, cabbage, garlic powder and soy sauce. Cook until tender. Cool and drain.

title: fruit salad or dessert
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple juice and Tang. Mix with fruit and let chill. Just before serving, add bananas and nuts to garnish.

title: homemade hot dog sauce
directions: Cook ground beef with the onion, tomatoes, pepper and salt. Add the chili powder.
Cook for about 10 minutes. Add puree.
Let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef until brown.
Drain.
Add Village Saucery and continue cooking over medium-low heat.
Put some lettuce in a large bowl.
Add diced tomatoes.
Put ground beef mix into large bowl.
Stir all ingredients together.
Crunch up tortilla chips and sprinkle in salad.
Add taco sauce on top.
If you choose, you can also add sour cream with taco sauce.

title: fresh pea soup
directions: Add all ingredients except cream to blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Before serving, put blended ingredients into a large pot, bring to a boil and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Add the cream, heating again to boiling.
Season to taste.
May also add diced and cooked carrots, potatoes and ham.
Or serve sprinkled with chopped fried bacon.
Serve hot or cold.
Yields 9 servings.

title: pecan crescent dessert
directions: Pour over the partially baked crescent rolls and bake 20 to 25 minutes until brown.

title: mock apple ring
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over drained cucumbers in large container with tight-fitting lid.
A large Tupperware works well. Let set 24 hours.
Drain liquid.
Reheat and pour it back over cucumbers each day for 3 days.
On the 4th day, reheat liquid and cucumbers to boiling.
Fill sterilized jars and seal.

title: low calorie soup
directions: Cook together until cabbage and carrots are tender.

title: citrus grilled salmon
directions: Cut salmon in serving sized pieces.
To make marinade:
Combine all of the other ingredients in a small non-metal bowl.
Put salmon in a large non-metal container and pour the marinade over the fish. Marinade the fish for 10 minutes on each side.
Discard the marinade.
Place fish on a hot grill and cook for 4 minutes on each side or broil 8 minutes on each side until fork tender.
Can be doubled for 4-6 pounds of salmon.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add corn syrup and water. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Fill baked pie shell with fresh strawberries.
Pour cooled mixture over strawberries.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: onion dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Serve with Ritz crackers, chips or Fritos.

title: cheese shrimpball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans until well blended.
Form into a ball and roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers or rye bread.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Sieve flours and sugar into a mixing bowl.
Add butter; knead and squeeze into the dry ingredients using one hand only until mixture is combined to a smooth, stiff dough.
Roll dough out on a lightly floured surface to a 1/4-inch thickness, using gentle even pressure with a lightly floured rolling pin.
Cut into rounds with a 2-inch cutter.
Repeat rolling and cutting until all the mixture is used.
Place rounds on greased baking tray.
Prick well and place in refrigerator to rest for at least 30 minutes.
Bake in 300° to 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until light golden.
Allow to set on baking trays before removing to a wire cooling tray. Store in airtight container.

title: mexican cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 2 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Let cool.

title: saucy beef cubes
directions: Brown meat in oil; pour off drippings.
Add salt, pepper, celery seed, bay leaf, basil and water.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 2 hours.
Add tomato juice and onions and continue cooking for 45 minutes or until meat is tender and onions are done. Remove meat and onions.
Discard bay leaf.
Measure cooking liquid and add enough water to make 1 1/4 cups.
Thicken liquid with flour for gravy.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: A good gumbo starts with a roux, a cooked mixture of flour and grease (lard, shortening or oil).

title: chef jerry's shrimp etouffee(a-too-fay)
directions: Can substitute boneless, skinless chicken breast for the shrimp.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Lightly brown meat and onion in frying pan, salt and pepper. When browned, add chicken soup.
Pare and slice potatoes. Put layer in bottom of buttered casserole.
Cover with a layer of meat, then another layer of potatoes.
Pour enough milk over all to show around edges.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven until potatoes are done.
Serve with a crisp salad for a complete meal.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, milk and flavoring; beat well.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Shape into mound in waxed paper and chill thoroughly.
Roll on lightly floured board until dough is about 1/4-inch thick.
Dip cutter in confectioners sugar each time before cutting cookie, then place cookie on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 dozen medium-sized cookies.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix first 5 items in order given.
Put in greased pan.
Mix corn flakes and 1/3 cup margarine; put over potatoes.
Bake 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip bar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In a small bowl, combine flour, wheat germ, baking soda and salt; mix well. In large bowl, beat together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla, mixing until well blended. Gradually add flour mixture; mix well. Stir in chocolate pieces. Spread
into a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on wire rack. Cut into 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch bars. Makes 42 bars.

title: cranberry sauce for meatballs
directions: Bake meatballs.
Meanwhile, combine cranberry sauce and cream of tomato soup, undiluted.
Heat through.
Add meatballs and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.
May also be used as an appetizer.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix all the above ingredients and refrigerate or freeze. Crushed pecans may also be added.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix sugar and flour, then add to pineapple. Add cheese.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix butter and crackers together.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir sugar, salt and corn syrup together in a 1 3/4-quart dish.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir well and add peanuts. Cook on High for 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Add vanilla, butter and soda.
Stir and cook on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes longer.
Stir and pour on greased cookie sheet.
Cool 1/2 hour; break in pieces.

title: dick goddard's woolly bear chili
directions: Crumble and brown ground beef in heavy skillet (no fat added). Add onion and green pepper; cook until almost tender.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover.
Simmer gently 2 hours, adding bean liquid and water, a little at a time if needed, to keep consistency of thick soup.
Add kidney beans; heat through.
Remove bay leaves. Serve in small bowls.
Yields 6 servings.

title: no-knead rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve the yeast in the lukewarm water. Add sugar, salt and about half of the flour.
Beat thoroughly for 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening.
Gradually beat in remaining flour until smooth.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil but do not boil!
Soften gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water and mix with cooked ingredients.
Put in refrigerator to thicken.
Add celery, Velveeta cheese and pecans.
Blend all into whipped cream.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cheese cake for dieters
directions: Mix graham crackers and margarine together.
Press into pie pan and chill.

title: eight can soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Put everything in a large crock-pot.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Use vinegar water and get it real sweet with 2 cups sugar; get it boiling.

title: old fashioned lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and lemon juice with one cup of water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved, then add remaining water.
Serve over ice.
Makes about 8 servings.
For pink lemonade, add cherry juice.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips and margarine, in a large mixing bowl.
Transfer mixture to a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle crushed chips evenly over mixture.
Drizzle margarine over chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Try this.
It's very good!

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Crumble bacon on bottom of pastry shell; add onion, then add Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs; add half and half milk along with flour and dry mustard.
Add a dash of cayenne pepper.
Pour into pastry shell and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nothing cookies
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Fold in sugar and nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet, covered with greased foil.
Preheat oven to 250° and cook for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave in oven 30 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and dice maraschino cherries. Put softened cream cheese in mixing bowl. Add sugar, salt, Miracle Whip and lemon juice. Blend well. Fold in Cool Whip. Add fruit and nuts. Pour in dish and freeze. Keeps a long time in the freezer. When ready to serve, thaw slightly. Can be re-frozen if needed.

title: baby food pound cake
directions: Grease
and
flour
tube pan.
Put all ingredients into one bowl.
Stir
all
ingredients together and bake at 350° to 375° about 1 hour.
Decorate with sprinkles or powdered sugar.

title: spicy toasted pecans
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Set aside.
Beat egg white in large bowl.
Stir in pecans and coat thoroughly.
Add sugar mixture and stir pecans until well coated.
Spread pecans in shallow baking dish or on cookie or pizza pan.
Spread out as much as possible.
Bake in moderate oven (350°), stirring frequently until toasted (15 to 20 minutes).
Pecans should be mostly dry when done.
Let cool for a few minutes and remove from pan.
If they stay too long, it's hard to get them off.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour on heated shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients well; spread mixture in a greased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.
Cut into rectangles about 2 x 1-inch.
Refrigerate remaining appetizers; reheat when serving remainder.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with applesauce, mixing well.
Add nuts and raisins, which have been rolled in flour.
Bake in moderate oven for 70 minutes in loaf or tube cake pan.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk in baking dish.
Pour sweet fruit on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: slice and bake oatmeal cookies
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, oats and salt and set aside. In a large bowl, cream butter until soft and fluffy; blend in extracts.
Gradually add oat mixture and mix well.
Shape into one 12-inch roll about 2-inches thick.
Roll in chopped pecans, pressing nuts into outside of roll.
Wrap securely and refrigerate several hours, or until very firm.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices, re-shaping into rounds if necessary.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove with spatula and cool on rack.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add juice, pears and cottage cheese in appropriate bowl.
Chill.

title: citrus snow mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine orange juice and ice cubes to make 1 1/2 cups.
Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in Cool Whip and stir until well mixed.
Pour into a 5-cup mold sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Chill until very firm. Serve with raspberries.

title: hot applesauce cake
directions: Heat applesauce.
Melt shortening in applesauce; add sugar, dry ingredients, nuts and raisins.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pans at 325° approximately 1 hour.
This is an old-timer's recipe. Keeps well and can be frozen.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add soda to 1/2 cup buttermilk; mix well.
Add to butter mixture.
Add flour and rest of buttermilk. Add vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn into large loaf pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours, or until done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour half of the batter into black iron skillet.
Top with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Pour rest of batter and top with remainder of the cheese.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Start with ham pieces in water.
Add peas and other ingredients; bring to boil.
Turn down; cook until done.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: *Butter and eggs should be at room temperature.

title: chocolate fudge upside-down cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add milk and stir.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Stir well and add to mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch buttered pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: tasty chicken pie
directions: Boil
chicken
in water until tender along with celery, onions,
carrots, salt and pepper.
Strain chicken and vegetables reserving broth.
Bone chicken.
Heat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in 11
x
13 x 2-inch dish; place chicken in.
Add cooked vegetables and
peas.
Combine
baking
mix
with milk and mix until smooth. Pour baking mix over top of chicken and vegetables.
Pour
chicken broth over all.
Bake until golden brown about 35 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, oil, baking soda, salt and vanilla together.
Add fruit cocktail.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef (raw), egg and uncooked rice portion of box.
Form into small meatballs and brown on all sides in frying pan over medium heat.
When browned evenly, pour 2 3/4 cups water over meatballs and sprinkle beef flavor seasoning packet (from rice box) over all. Cover and cook over low heat until water cooks away, about 20 minutes.
Turn meatballs occasionally for thorough cooking.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Put your macaroni in saucepan; put oil and chopped onion in skillet.
When onion turns yellow, add tomato and salt and beef. Let simmer for 5 minutes, then add macaroni and let all simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla in mixing bowl; heat thoroughly.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to shortening mixture.
Mix well.
Blend in oats and drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet or wok, melt margarine.
When hot, pour in chicken pieces, salt and pepper.
Cook
until chicken is tender. Add other ingredients, stirring occasionally, for 3 or 4 minutes. Add 2 cups Minute rice and 1 can chicken broth.
Mix and bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Let set until rice is done, usually 5 minutes.

title: mexican pizza dip
directions: Spread soft cream cheese on round serving tray.
Top with salsa, then shredded cheese.
Serve with Doritos.
Top with sliced olives.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Fill cup 1/3 to 1/2 full of this mixture.
Fill with hot water.

title: cheese puffies
directions: Cream the cheese and oleo.
Work in flour and cayenne.
Chill and shape into small balls.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 450° oven on cookie sheet.
Cool slightly before removing.
Serve warm or cool.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Measure 1/2 cup of mixture and blend into thawed Cool Whip and sugar.
Chill Cool Whip until firm enough to mound. Spread over bottom and up sides of an 8 or 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Add strawberry halves to remaining Jell-O mix and gently spoon on top of Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Arrange lettuce on serving dish.
Top with rest of vegetables and sausage.
Add cheese and pour Italian dressing over salad.
Serve immediately.

title: rice-coated beef balls
directions: Cover rice with water and set aside.
In mixing bowl combine egg, garlic, salt, ginger and pepper.
Add ground beef and onion and mix well.
Shape meat mixture into 24 meatballs.
Drain rice, roll meatballs in rice until coated.
Over high heat, bring water for steaming to boiling.
Put meatballs on greased steamer rack, leaving space between them.
Place over boiling water, cover 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix remaining ingredients together; add to butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: salami
directions: Mix thoroughly; cover and refrigerate.
Knead once daily for 3 days.
Place in 2 loaf pans and pack down.
Bake at 150° for 10 hours.
Eat or freeze.

title: pastry
directions: Sift together into bowl the flour, salt and sugar.
Using a pastry blender, cut the shortening into the flour until it resembles corn meal.
Add milk, 1 tablespoon at a time, and just enough to make particles stick together.
Roll out 1/2 of pastry, fill pie pan and brush with melted butter.
Add fruit filling. Roll out remainder of pastry and place on top of pie.

title: mexican stir
directions: Cook ground round in pan; add beans, corn, cheese, taco mix and taco salsa.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with corn chips.

title: barbecued country spareribs
directions: Thaw and trim country spareribs.
Put 1 tablespoon of salt in quart of water and boil ribs in a covered pot for 1 hour.
Cook slowly over low flame.
Drain water.
Put into shallow roasting pan.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix in bowl the molasses, mustard, garlic powder, hot sauce, tomato paste and vinegar.
Pour mixture over spareribs.
Cover.
Place into oven.
Cook until tender, about 1
hour.

title: fruity macaroon cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, salt, almond extract, lemon rind and egg and beat until well blended.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda into bowl with first mixture and mix until blended.
Add cherries and coconut and mix.
Drop by tablespoon on greased baking sheets.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: french chicken
directions: Cook, debone and chop chicken; reserve broth.
Cook onions, celery, parsley and peppers in about 3 cups broth until tender. Cook noodles in broth until tender.
Add tomato sauce, garlic, olives, mushrooms and Worcestershire sauce and mix well.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
For extra broth, boil skin and bones.
Freezes well.

title: marinated fish filets
directions: Combine all ingredients (except for fish filets) and marinate fish filets in the mixture for 1/2 hour or more.
Broil 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve with tartar sauce.

title: honey steak
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
Adjust amounts to taste.
Brush on steaks as they are grilled.

title: monkey bars(no bake cookie)
directions: Combine marshmallows, honey, butter, peanut butter, vanilla and salt in medium saucepan.
Melt marshmallow mixture over low heat, stirring constantly.
Combine in a separate bowl; rice cereal, oats, coconut and peanuts.
Pour marshmallow mixture over dry ingredients and mix thoroughly until coated well.
Press mixture firmly into 13x9 inch pan.
Cool completely before cutting.
Makes about 2 doz. bars.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix apples, oranges, pineapple, marshmallows, raisins, pecans, sour cream and sugar.
Top with coconut and maraschino cherries.

title: big mac sauce
directions: Blend with fork and refrigerate.
Good for two dozen burgers.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Sift the flour onto a piece of waxed paper.
Measure 1 1/2 cups of this flour into a large bowl.

Stir in the active yeast. In a saucepan, place the milk, water, salad oil, sugar and salt. Set over low heat and heat only until warm, stirring to blend. Add liquid ingredients to flour and yeast in bowl and beat until smooth.
Blend in the eggs.
Add enough additional flour to make a stiff batter, beating until smooth and elastic.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half; arrange in baking dish. Combine sugar, margarine, salt and water in pan and boil 5 minutes.
Add orange rind.
Pour over potatoes. Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Remove; arrange bananas around baking dish and bake 12 to 15 minutes longer.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Cut butter into mixture with pastry blender.
Spoon mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; press down evenly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Combine 1 cup flour and baking powder.
Add eggs, 2 cups sugar and lemon juice.
Beat well. Pour over baked crust and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned and set.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup powdered sugar and cut into bars when cool.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: monkey bread
directions: Slice biscuits 4 ways.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in Ziploc bag. Add biscuit pieces to mixture a few at a time.
Shake until covered will with mix.
Arrange in greased Bundt pan (don't use tube or you will lose glaze around bottom).
Put remaining biscuits in pan and pour rest of glaze and nuts over them.

title: favorite stew
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover and place in 250° oven for 4 hours or simmer in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours on low or 4 to 5 hours on high.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Grind cranberries with 1/2 of a whole orange, without seeds. Dissolve sugar, orange jello and plain gelatin in boiling water.

title: spiced pumpkin custard
directions: In quart microwave-safe bowl, combine all ingredients, except the large egg and large egg white.
Microwave, uncovered, on Medium for 3 minutes.

title: tarragon tomatoes
directions: Arrange tomatoes in shallow baking dish that just holds the halves, nicely snuggled together.
Sprinkle a little sugar over tomato halves.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake uncovered in preheated 375° oven for about 1/2 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peas oriental
directions: Barely cook and drain peas.
Add soup.
Drain and slice water chestnuts.
Drain bean sprouts.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Mix all together and bake 30 minutes.
Top with onion rings and bake 15 minutes more when ready to serve.
Will serve 6 to 8.

title: grooms cakes
directions: Several hours ahead, prepare the fruit mixture by mixing the first 9 ingredients; bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Reduce to low heat; simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool to room temperature (this takes about 2 hours).

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next three ingredients; spread over first mixture in pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Test in center for doneness.

title: crab cakes (angelina's restaurant)
directions: Blend the egg, mayo, baking powder, mustard and Old Bay seasoning.
Soak the bread slices in the milk, parsley and black pepper mixture for 5 minutes.
Add all ingredients to the first mixture.
Add crabmeat last.
Mix with fork and form into cakes. Broil 8 to 10 minutes or bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Pour butter over cake mix in mixing bowl.
Add pineapple; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes or until cake is done.
May serve with ice cream or whipped topping, if desired.

title: grandpa's fudge
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, combine sugar, milk, corn syrup and chocolate and heat mixture until boiling, STIRRING CONSTANTLY.
If using a candy thermometer, set it in place and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until the temperature reaches about 238°.
If no thermometer, cook until a small amount of the mixture dropped in very cold water forms a soft ball. Remove from heat; immediately add butter and vanilla.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion in melted margarine until tender.
Add soups and rice and stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Put tomato slices and onion slices in a shallow container. Combine oil, vinegar and garlic powder; shake well and pour over tomatoes and onions.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 30 minutes.
Serve on lettuce leaves or two pieces of toast.
Yum Yum.

title: fudge candy and chocolate drops
directions: Melt candy in microwave.
Add peanut butter and stir.
Drop onto wax paper and cool.

title: spicy cheese drops
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Preheat oven at 350°.
In medium bowl, cream margarine and cheese; stir in dry ingredients, nuts and seeds.
Roll spoonful of dough into balls; place on greased cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes until golden.
Yields 50 balls.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Combine crumbs and salt.
Dip chicken in milk and coat with crumbs mixture.
Place in single layer on nonstick coating-sprayed baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Do not cover pan or turn chicken while baking.
Serves 6.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Saute the roughly chopped onion in oil until light brown.
Add the onion to a large soup pot.
Add the chicken broth, chopped cauliflower and broccoli to the onion.
Add all of the spices. Simmer the soup (but do not let the soup boil) for 1 hour.
When the vegetables are soft, remove the soup from the stove and cool. Puree the cooled soup.
Return to the pot, reheat and serve.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix pineapple, flour, sugar and butter together.
Bring to boil; set aside and cool.
When cool, pour into glass container. Spread with Cool Whip and nuts.
This is better if made a day ahead.

title: family casserole - burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Mix ground beef with evaporated milk.
Divide into 5 patties.
On waxed paper, flatten each patty to form 6-inch circles.
Spoon 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each.
Draw edges over stuffing and seal.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine mushroom soup, Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 5. To vary, add a can of green beans.

title: pork chops with carmelized apples
directions: Pat chops dry.
Mix together thyme, pepper and salt and season both sides of all chops.
Set chops aside.
In a large, heavy skillet, melt the butter with the sugar over moderately high heat; add the apples and saute the mixture for 30-40 minutes, or until they begin to brown.
Turn the apples, cook them for 5 minutes more, or until golden brown and the sauce is thickened. remove from heat and keep warm.
Heat another heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Brush with a little vegetable oil.
Add chops and brown on one side about 4 minutes; turn and brown the other side 4 minutes more.
Keep turning chops every couple of minutes until just done (internal temperature measured with a meat thermometer will reach 160°).
Total cooking time for chops will be around 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve chops immediately with caramelized apples.

title: fried zucchini rounds
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add eggs and zucchni.
Use 2 tablespoons for each round. Brown in oil on both sides.

title: clam pie
