directions: Mix together.
Put in pie dish.
Squeeze lemon on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: firehouse pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place roast on double thickness of foil. Pour canned soup over meat and sprinkle on soup mix.
Wrap meat entirely in foil.
Place in shallow pan and cook for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
The juices from the meat will blend with the soups and produce a gravy.
Serves 6.

title: apple pie
directions: Cook fresh apples until half done in 1 cup of water.
Thicken this mixture with cornstarch and 1/4 cup water.
Mix with brown sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top crust can be cut in strips.
Lay across the pie vertically, then horizontally.
Brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and white sugar.

title: tile cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar until very light and fluffy.
Beat in flour, vanilla and almonds.
Drop by teaspoonful on a buttered cookie sheet rather far apart.
Flatten with a spoon.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven and let stand for 3 minutes.
Remove with spatula.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into one-inch squares.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and herbs.
Dip chicken into margarine and roll in crumb mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: mom's slaw dressing
directions: Cook until thickened.
Cool and put over shredded cabbage.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread the pie filling, then pineapple, then dry cake mix.
Cut butter into pats and place on dry cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans on top.
Bake at 375° until cake mix is done.

title: ball park beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Add hamburger and continue to brown. Drain off excess fat.
Put in bean pot or casserole and add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cape cod apple pie
directions: Mix apples, cranberry sauce, sugar, and tapioca all together. Pour into crust.
Place second crust on top and seal edges.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: spanish sunrise rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish and cook at 325° for about 50 minutes. Serves 8.

title: edith harris' asparagus casserole
directions: Alternate layers of asparagus, eggs, pimento and sauce.
Top with cornflake crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Once mixed together, stir in cake chunks.
Slice 1 quart strawberries.
Stir slices into 2 packages of strawberry glaze. Then spread over the cake mixture.
Chill for several hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Boil all ingredients for 20 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, salt, flour and soda.
Set aside.
Mix egg, oil and vanilla.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Stir in apples.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° preheated oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: In mixing bowl mix cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt.
Beat until mixture is smooth.
Add 1 egg and beat until mixed well.
Pour the mixture over bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Then layer pecans evenly over mixture.
Set aside.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole dish. Mix corn flakes and margarine.
Sprinkle on top of potato mixture. Cook for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: quick spinach dip
directions: Steam spinach until tender; drain water.
Chop up finely. Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, water, butter, peanut butter and half of the cake mix (dry) until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix and the chocolate pieces.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce for meatballs
directions: Double sauce recipe for 1/2 bag of Italian meatballs from Sam's Wholesale.
Place meatballs in crock-pot and pour sauce over them.
Let simmer until hot.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook slowly until it cooks down and starts to thicken.
I put in jars and seal them.

title: indian fry bread
directions: In small bowl, mix flour, baking powder and milk.
Form dough into ball.
On lightly floured board, knead until smooth, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes.
Make into 8 balls. Fry one at a time for 1 minute.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly. Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder and salt and sift together 3 times.
Add flour mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add flavoring.
Chill.
Roll dough very thin and cut into fancy shapes with floured cutter.
Decorate tops of cookies with sugar, colored candies, finely powdered walnuts, almonds, whole blanched almonds and raisins.
Bake on well greased cookie sheets or on bottom of inverted pans in a hot oven (400°) 6 minutes or until done.
Watch that they do not burn!
Makes about 10 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: quailcrest baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet and crumble. Saute the onion in the bacon fat.
Combine everything together in bean pot.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours or 375° for 1 1/2 hours. Good warm or cold.

title: sour cherry muffins
directions: Pit cherries and drain.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar (3 tablespoons).
In a bowl, combine the egg, milk and oil. Pour into dry ingredients all at once.
Stir until dry ingredients are moist, but still lumpy, about 17 to 25 strokes.
To the drained cherries, add 1/4 cup sugar and the cinnamon.
Gently fold into batter.
Spoon batter into lightly buttered muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: kat's easy hamburger pie
directions: Add 1 teaspoon salt to hamburger and brown; add chopped onion and cook until tender.
Drain.
Cook macaroni; add 1 teaspoon salt to water, until done; drain.
Mix mushroom soup, hamburger and noodles together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven, grate cheese on top.
Bake for an additional 10 minutes until cheese melts.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Separate eggs and beat yolks slightly.
Cream margarine and sugar together until crumbly.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add lemon juice, rind and corn meal.
Beat egg whites until firm but not stiff.
Fold whites into other ingredients.
Pour into deep dish unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° until firm but not stiff.

title: moist pineapple cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Stir in pineapple, baking soda, baking powder, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Add flour and nuts. Drop onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden around the edges.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in butter.
Add diced tomatoes and seasonings; stir well.
Add water, carrots and potatoes, tomato sauce and wine.
Cook until potatoes and carrots are tender.
Add vegetables and simmer.
Yields 12 quarts.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix well together.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or 325° for glass dish.
You can put a thin confectioners sugar glaze on warm cake if desired.

title: creamy potato casserole
directions: Peel, dice and boil potatoes, then cool potatoes.
Melt butter and undiluted soup in saucepan.
Cool slightly.
Turn cooled potatoes into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, save 1 1/2 c. pineapple juice.
Cut peaches in 1/2 inch cubes.
Combine fruit, marshmallows and ginger.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat pineapple juice to boiling.
Add gelatin; stir to dissolve.
Add orange juice and lemon juice, sugar and salt; stir to dissolve.
Chill.

title: pasta pesto with vegetables
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Saute broccoli and carrots in olive oil 2 minutes; add onions and garlic.
Saute for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients; saute is al dente.
Toss with cooked pasta and Parmesan cheese.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk(like eagle brand)
directions: Blend in blender.
Receipt can be doubled.
One receipt equals 1 can Eagle Brand milk.

title: coconut-chocolate chip bars
directions: Prepare frosting mix according to package directions, adding vanilla. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: sweet 'n sour shrimp
directions: Combine pineapple juice, water, lemon juice, sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce and ginger in saucepan.
Heat over medium heat until thick, add shrimp and remaining ingredients.
Serve over rice.

title: a fruit dip
directions: With a blender beat cream cheese and sour cream. Then add all other ingredients and mix well; chill.

title: roast goose with port-thyme gravy
directions: Discard goose liver.
Chop reserved heart and gizzards.
Cut neck into 2-inch lengths.
Heat oil in heavy, large Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add heart, gizzards and neck; saute until brown, about 15 minutes.
Add onions, carrots, thyme sprigs, parsley and bay leaves; saute until golden, scraping bottom of pan occasionally, about 20 minutes.
Add 3 cups broth and 2 cups water. Bring to simmer.
Cover partially; simmer for 1 hour and 15 minutes, skimming surface occasionally.
Strain stock into large glass measuring cup; discard solids.
Skim any fat from surface of stock.
Add more chicken broth to stock if necessary to measure 4 cups.
Set aside.
(Can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.)

title: avocado green chili dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and puree in an electric blender. Transfer to a serving bowl and place avocado seeds in the center of the dip until ready to serve.
(This will prevent the dip from turning brown.)
Chill and serve with chips.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix water, vinegar and egg together and beat well.
Set aside. Mix
flour,
Crisco
and
salt with fork until it looks like meal. Add
liquid,
stirring
with fork until it forms a ball. Divide into 3 equal parts.
Makes 3 pie crust.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger, onion and bacon.
Stir all together. Bake in baking dish for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Bake uncovered.

title: honeymoon salad
directions: Mix the ingredients and top with Dream Whip.

title: curry chicken
directions: Wash poultry very clean.
In a skillet, add butter until melted, then add oil.
Put chicken in large bowl.
Add other ingredients, tossing chicken in seasoning.
Put chicken in hot skillet.
Turn until brown or well done.
Drain oil and serve. Good with spicy rice and salad.

title: eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add water and salt. Boil until tender. Cook onion in butter until light yellow.
Add eggplant, 2 cups bread crumbs and milk.
Put in casserole dish and cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sauce for yellow cake
directions: Cook until butter is melted.
Pour over cake while cake is warm.

title: tiny biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Fill muffin pans 2/3 full (large or small pans). Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown. Remove biscuits from pans immediately.

title: potatoes au gratin and kielbasa(a polish potluck supper)
directions: Prepare potato au gratin mix in large casserole dish according to box directions.
Slice kielbasa link; add to casserole.
Chop frozen broccoli; add to casserole.
Stir.
Bake according to box directions, approximately 20 minutes.
Makes family size casserole dinner!

title: torte
directions: Make crust first.
Roll crackers finely.
Add sugar and margarine.
Mix well.
Place 3/4 of the graham crackers in a 7 x 11-inch pan.

title: grandma's sweet buns
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well. Let rise until doubled in size.
Make into rolls.
Put in greased cake pan.
Let rise again.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery.
Add drained broccoli, cooked rice, soups, cheese and seasonings.
Bake at 375° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Put milk in kettle.
Set kettle in larger pan with water. Heat to boiling.
Beat eggs and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat well; put rest of sugar in hot milk.
Add 1 cup of hot milk to eggs.
Beat well, then pour slowly through a strainer into hot milk.
Cook 10 minutes; never let boil.
Stir while cooking.
Add vanilla to taste.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: creamy chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, rice, soup, chicken and cream cheese in bowl, mixing well.
Spoon into casserole.
Pour milk over casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans, place in baking dish, mix in soup, if necessary add a little milk or liquid from the green beans.

title: prune drop cookies(1933 recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Drop with teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Place 1/2 teaspoon Date Filling on dough; cover with another 1/2 teaspoon of dough.
Bake until lightly browned, 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: italian chicken crock pot style
directions: Place the chicken in crock pot. Sprinkle the dry mix spaghetti sauce over the top. Add the can of tomatoes & the can of tomato sauce. Cook all day on low or 1/2 day on high. Serve with pasta and top with parmesan cheese.

title: rotel spicy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine first 7 ingredients. Spread into ungreased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour. Drain excess drippings. Spoon chili sauce over cooked loaf. Bake another 15 minutes. Serves 8.

title: caramel apples
directions: Melt caramels with water in a double boiler over low heat. Stir occasionally until sauce is smooth. Wash and dry apples. Insert a stick in stem end of each. Dip into hot caramel sauce or spoon it on until coated.
Place on buttered wax paper. Chill until firm.

title: fudge-nut bars
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Add baking soda, 1 teaspoon salt, flour and then the oatmeal; set aside.
In a double boiler, combine chocolate chips, sweetened condensed milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt and butter and melt until smooth.
Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Spread 2/3 of first mixture on a large jelly roll pan.
Cover with chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle the rest on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: brown gravy
directions: In medium saucepan, stir flour into hot butter until smooth. Cook, stirring over low heat, to brown flour slightly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in broth.
Bring to boiling, stirring. Reduce heat; simmer 1 to 2 minutes, until thickened.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla (beat in egg whites).
Last, blend in Ritz crackers and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes in greased pie pan.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownies according to directions on package. Cool and poke holes; pour Kahlua over brownies. Crumble and place 1/2 in large bowl. Prepare mousse according to directions and divide into 2 equal portions. Spread 1/2 the mousse over the crumbled brownies; spread 1/2 the Cool Whip over mousse. Crush the Heath bars and nuts and sprinkle over the Cool Whip. Repeat all steps. Refrigerate and allow to set for several hours or overnight for flavors to mingle. Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit, marshmallows and cream together.
Beat egg, sugar and vinegar together and cook in double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and mustard, mix well.
(Fruit can be substituted or more added according to taste.)
Pour cooled dressing over fruit, adding bananas just before serving. 10 to 12 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except French fried onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes or until onions are golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 4-star broccoli salad
directions: Cut florets off the stalks; wash and drain.
Peel outer tough layers off the stalks.
Chop up center of stalks.
Mix with chopped up bacon, onion and raisins.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and shape into a ring in a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out and pour sauce over it.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes longer.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Stir all well.
Pour into baked crust or graham cracker crust. Set 3 hours.
Top with whipped topping.

title: chocolate chews
directions: In heavy 2
quart saucepan mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk. Stir over
medium
heat
until mixture bubbles all over the top. Boil and
stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat and stir in until blended,
cup
peanut butter, vanilla, uncooked rolled oats and
nut
meats (coconut too, if desired). Drop by 2 teaspoons on wax paper until set.

title: berry valentine pie
directions: On bottom of pie crust, spread strawberries evenly; cover with whipped cream.
Spread cherries on whipped cream and spread whipped cream layer on top.
Spread blueberries on whipped cream then top with remaining whipped cream.
Sprinkle crumbled crackers on top of pie and place in the refrigerator for 45 minutes.
Serve and enjoy.

title: pizza in the round(children's)
directions: Have an adult help you cut the bagel in half.
Spread pizza sauce or spaghetti sauce over the 2 halves.
Add Cheddar cheese or you can use Velveeta cheese slices or shredded Cheddar cheese. Place in microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes (1:30 - 2:00 minutes).
Be careful when removing.
Pizzas will be very hot.
Let them cool for about 1 minute and then eat and enjoy.
Serves 1.

title: mangoade
directions: Rub the mango through a sieve. Heat sugar, water and orange rind, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Cool. Add sugar, syrup and fruit juices to the mango puree, stirring well. Refrigerate. Serve in tall glasses over ice. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine butter and cheese until well blended.
Add salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix in flour (will be a dry consistency). Form into 2 logs 1 1/2-inches round.
Wrap tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix the mashed potatoes, sugar, butter or margarine, eggs, vanilla and milk in large bowl.

title: beverly's coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box.
Cool completely. Slice layers in half.
Mix coconut, sour cream and powdered sugar thoroughly until all sugar is dissolved.
Spread between layers and on top.
refrigerate for 48 hours.
If desired put coconut on sides and top of cake with hands.

title: duke's brownies
directions: Make brownies according to directions with nuts.
When cool, top with mixture of confectioners sugar, 1/2 cup soft butter and creme de menthe; spread like icing and refrigerate.
When cool and set, melt the chocolate chips and 6 tablespoons of butter.
Spread like icing on green layer and refrigerate until set.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Cream together 2 sticks oleo, 2 cups sugar and flour. Add eggs and vanilla (2 tablespoons) to creamed mixture. Add 2 tablespoons cocoa, coconut and nuts; mix well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Let cool, then spread marshmallow cream on top.

title: stove top rice pudding
directions: Simmer milk and rice over very low heat.
Mix sugar, eggs and salt in blender.
Add to milk and rice.
Simmer a little longer until thickened.
Sprinkle with ground nutmeg.

title: meat ball casserole
directions: Add onion and garlic to hamburger; form into balls.
Brown slowly.
Place in baking dish.
Add soup and water.
Bake covered for 1 hour, or until potatoes are done.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: While hot, cut baked potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out insides; whip potatoes.
Add margarine.
Gradually beat in milk. Stir in onion, salt and pepper.
Spoon back into shells.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: tif's rock bars
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, mix butter, both sugars and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, soda and salt.
Mix both mixtures and add nuts. Spread batter into pan and sprinkle chocolate chips over the top. Bake in a 375° oven for 1 minute.
Remove.
Use a knife to create a marble effect on top.
Return to oven for 13 to 16 minutes or until golden brown.

title: raspberry bavarian
directions: Place hot water in 2-cup measure.
Microwave at High for 2 to 2 3/4 minutes or until water boils.
Place gelatin in medium mixing bowl.
Stir in boiling water.
Stir to dissolve gelatin. Mix in cold water.
Chill until gelatin is soft set, about 1 hour. Place raspberries in 1-quart casserole.
Cover.
Microwave at 50% (Medium) for 3 to 5 minutes or until raspberries are defrosted, stirring once.
Reserve 6 whole berries for garnishing, if desired.
Stir raspberries into gelatin.
Set aside.
Place egg white in small mixing bowl.
Beat at high speed of an electric mixer until stiff peaks form.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Fold 1 cup whipped topping into gelatin mixture.
Spoon into each of 6 stemmed glasses or dessert dishes.
Top evenly with remaining 1/2 cup whipped topping.
Garnish with raspberries.
Serve immediately or chill for 1 hour for firmer texture.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all well, then roll into balls.
Roll balls in colored sprinkles.
Store overnight.

title: marinated corn
directions: Mix together.
Pour over corn.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Will keep several days.

title: double coconut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into well greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mac and cheese
directions: Have your mom make the macaroni on the stove.
Drain off the water and rinse the macaroni.
Put in the cheese they give you and 1/2 stick of oleo.
Stir it up until the cheese melts and the butter melts.
Let your kids eat it right away before it gets glumpy.
If there is any left, put it in the fridge.
When you microwave the leftovers, put in some milk so it gets creamy. Mario's is better.

title: cucumber and mint butter
directions: Combine butter, salad burnet and mint.
Spread the mint and butter on the bread slices.
Lay the cucumber on half of the bread slices.
Trim off crust and cut diagonally.

title: rosalynn carter's "plains special" cheese ring
directions: Combine cheese, nuts, onion and pepper.
Add mayonnaise and blend well.
Line 3 to 4-cup mold with plastic wrap, allowing enough overlap to seal.
Pat cheese mixture into mold firmly. Seal and chill.
Refrigerate until firm (several hours or overnight).
To serve, unmold and fill center with either preserves or green grapes.
Serve with crackers.

title: zesty beef
directions: Rub rib roast with salt, pepper, garlic powder or herbs or your choice.
Cook covered at 250° for 1 hour for each pound of meat, or use meat thermometer until rare.
Pour drippings over and serve.

title: microwave coronado casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken, sour cream and cheese. Cook on High for 10 minutes.
Stir after 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients, saving 1/2 of cheese.
Pour into greased baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with crushed corn chips.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: cocoa-mocha mousse
directions: Combine Ricotta cheese, yogurt and cocoa powder in container of food processor.
Whirl 2 minutes, until mixture is very smooth. Turn into medium-size bowl.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish.

title: black walnut and chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt together 3 times.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in black walnut extract and chocolate. Fold in walnuts.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 55 minutes.
Do not open oven door during baking time.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan and stir with a fork until blended.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.

title: crunchy chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: crazy pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet sprayed with Pam, saute meat.
Add vegetables.
Stir in tomato sauce, Sweet 'N Low and Italian seasoning.
Cut each unbaked biscuit into 4 pieces. Add to meat mixture; stir gently to combine.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish, greased.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Sprinkle shredded cheeses over top.
Continue to bake until cheese melts on top, about 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water; set aside.
Melt oleo in 1 cup boiling water.
Add sugar, then 1 cup cold water.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in yeast mixture; mix well and set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour and salt.
Add yeast mixture; blend well.
Knead in bowl.
Store dough in covered, greased bowl in refrigerator.
Make rolls as desired.
Let rise about 2 hours or doubled in bulk.
Dough keeps 3 days in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Add whipping cream to Bisquick substituting whipping cream for liquid.
Cut out and bake as usual.
Delicious.

title: portuguese cod(portuguese)
directions: Season cod with pepper and place in skillet. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for about 10 to 12 minutes. Remove cod pieces and keep warm. Continue to cook sauce for about 5 minutes.
Pour over fish and serve.
Preparation time:
about 15 minutes.
Cooking time:
about 20 minutes.

title: bubble loaf
directions: Melt oleo, brown sugar and cinnamon in microwave about 45 minutes.
Cut biscuits into fourths and roll in mixture.
Place in small baking dish.
Bake in microwave 3/4 minute.

title: holiday salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and let set overnight.
Add the remaining ingredients. Fold in 1 pint of whipping cream (may use Cool Whip).

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften while getting other ingredients together in bowl.
Dice one package smoked meat reserving the other package for later.
Combine cream cheese with diced meat, pepper, onions, olives and pimentos and mix well.
Form a ball of mixture and start to wrap ball with single slice of reserved meat. Continue wrapping ball until all of meat is used.
Chill.
Better if this sets overnight.

title: after-church stew
directions: Place beef (no need to brown) in 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with salt, basil and pepper.
Top with celery, carrots and onions.

title: black-bottom cake
directions: Beat well cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Mix in chocolate chips.
Set aside.
Mix well the remaining ingredients.
Pour in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drop cheese mixture on top of chocolate mixture by teaspoon.
Get into the corners.
Cover completely.
Put chopped English walnuts on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: yogurt fruit shakes
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Puree until strawberries are combined.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, pour into two pie crusts. Bake at 325° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with chopped onion.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Mix soup and water; spoon over, cover dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix everything together except water and yeast.
Stir yeast into water and add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
(Let rise once for a softer crust.)
Place on pizza pans, then add toppings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until just tender.
Drain and cool.
Cut onion and green pepper in round slices, then mix with carrots.
Mix all other ingredients together, then pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate 12 or more hours before serving.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, cheese, milk and salt; mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Add additional mayonnaise just before serving, if desired.
Serve on lettuce.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Drain carrots.
Combine other ingredients to make a sauce. Pour over carrots.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat thoroughly with bread, which has been soaked in the milk.
Add seasonings and beaten egg.
Mix well.
Spread into well-greased pan and bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Spread on tomato paste and continue baking 20 to 25 more minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In mixing bowl combine eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add pumpkin mixture and mix thoroughly. Spread batter on ungreased 15 x 10 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon lush cake(it's really a pie!)
directions: Mix together in a large pie tin the oleo
and graham cracker crumbs; pack well around sides.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Add eggs, sugar, butter and salt.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Beat after each cup.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Divide into 4 parts.
Roll out into circle like thick pie crust.
Cut into 6 wedges.
Brush with Mazola oil.
Roll from large end; drip in oil.
Let rise on greased pan until about double.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cinnamon sugar treats
directions: Remove pie crust from freezer and let thaw 10 to 20 minutes in pan.
Prick bottom and sides of thawed crust thoroughly with a fork.
Dot bottom and sides of thawed pie crust with 1 tablespoon softened butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 8 to 13 minutes or until golden brown. Let cool; then cut into pieces for serving.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and set aside.
In saucepan add milk, sugar, butter and salt.
Heat until butter is melted.
Cool until lukewarm, then add yeast mixture and flour and stir.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes in a warm place.
Place dough on floured surface and pat out until 3/4 inch thick.
Cut with a glass.
Add a pat of butter to each roll and fold over. Let stand 15 minutes, then bake for 10 minutes at 425°.
Makes 24 to 28 rolls.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix
ingredients together.
Pour into a casserole dish. Add crushed
Ritz
crackers on top; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients together; add this to your sugar-oil mixture.
Bake in a 3-pound loaf pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bar b que pineapple
directions: Take fresh pineapple, cut in long pieces. Take the core out and skin the rind off. Put the pineapple on aluminum foil. Cover pineapple with brown sugar and melted butter. Cook until tender.

title: hungry jack beef and bean round-up
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and baked beans.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Cut biscuits in half; put around sides of dish and then add cheese and bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate devil's food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9-inch round pans or 1 Bundt pan.
In large mixing bowl, cream sugar and margarine or butter. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix for 1 minute or until smooth.
In a small bowl, mix cocoa and coffee.
In a medium size bowl, mix flour, soda, salt and baking soda.
Alternate flour mixture and coffee mixture and mix into egg mixture until all mixed.
Pour into pans and bake 20 minutes for round pans or 40 to 45 minutes for Bundt pan.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Add egg with flour; dip pork cubes in batter and brown in hot oil.
Drain well; add to sauce.

title: garlic in oil
directions: Peel garlic cloves and blend in blender with olive oil.
Store in refrigerator in sealed jar.
Use when chopped garlic is called for.

title: chicken stir-fry in a bag
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and marinate for 1 hour.
Divide mixture in half and place each half on 2 sheets of foil, making hobo-dinner like packets.
Bake 20 minutes in 450 degree oven. Serve with rice.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Open hamburger buns and lay flat on cookie sheet.
Dice up pepper and onion in bowl; add sauce.
Brown hamburger; drain and add to mixture.
Spoon onto buns and top with the cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients, except zucchini.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add zucchini.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes until lightly browned.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Soak beans overnight; add soup, onion, liquid smoke and water. Cook until beans are tender.
Add brown sugar.
Place in casserole and warm 1/2 hour before serving.

title: angel pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix sugar, salt and baking powder; add to egg whites slowly and beat until it peaks.
Crush crackers and fold in.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into well buttered pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely and top with Cool Whip.

title: shrimp bake
directions: Mix above ingredients and bake in shallow dish for 20 minutes at 375°.
Serve with Triscuits or Tostitos.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil and keep medium boil for exactly 7 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Put in large bowl or pan the marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Pour boiled mixture over. Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat well until creamy.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: veggie pasta bake
directions: Mix spaghetti sauce, pasta, vegetables and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Spoon mixture into 9
x 13 baking dish or 3-quart casserole. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and remaining Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: sausage-potato casserole
directions: Peel, slice and cook potatoes until tender.
Crumble and brown sausage.
Drain.
In casserole dish, layer potatoes, sausage and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with cream of mushroom soup. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wall wash
directions: Mix together in a small pail and use.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients, buttermilk, oil, eggs, vanilla and vinegar.
Mix thoroughly. Spread batter in greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan; let cool.

title: chocolate kahlua trifle
directions: Make cake in 2 layers.
Make pudding.
When pudding is done, stir in Kahlua and cool.
Cut cake into cubes; will use less than both layers in standard trifle bowl.
Layer cake, pudding and Cool Whip.
Repeat.

title: chocolate chiffon cake
directions: Mix cocoa with boiling water; set aside.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until very stiff.
Set aside.
Sift dry ingredients.
Make well in center and add salad oil, egg yolks, cocoa mixture and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes, then at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add sour cream and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Sift again and add to first mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour half of batter into 8 x 12 greased pan.
Spread half of the topping over batter.

title: easy lemon dessert
directions: Mix all together except crackers and milk and set aside to jell like thick cream.
Take 1 (12 ounce) can evaporated milk, well chilled (almost icy), and whip into soft peaks.
Fold Jell-O mixture into whipped canned milk.
Pour into a lined 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan that has been lined with crushed graham crackers. Sprinkle few crumbs over the top and chill well.
Serves 12.

title: carrot bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together sugar, oil and eggs until smooth.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon, and carrots. Pour into ungreased 15x10-inch jelly roll pan, or two 9x13-inch pans. Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool completely before spreading frosting on top.

title: chicken pillows
directions: Mix cream
cheese,
butter and pepper.
Fold in chicken and mushrooms.
Roll
the stuffing mix until fine and mix with pecans. Unfold
crescent rolls and roll flat.
Put a spoonful of mixture in
center of wide area of the roll.
Roll and seal edges.
Dip in
melted
butter
and roll in stuffing mixture. Place in Dutch oven and bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Take thawed spinach and pat with paper towel to remove excess water. Combine all ingredients in crockpot and heat on low until creamy.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Combine and pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain and reserve
water, then debone salmon.
In large bowl combine all
ingredients
and
drop by teaspoonful in hot Crisco. Brown on both
sides
and drain well on paper towels. Makes 6 to 8 patties.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add eggs, oleo or butter, sour cream, corn and cream-style corn.
Blend until well blended with mixer.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: aunt bertha's stack cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; beat in eggs one at a time. Mix flour with soda, salt and spices. Add this alternately with sugar mixture and buttermilk. If batter seems too stiff, add a little more buttermilk. Put 3 large spoonfuls of batter in 8 or 9-inch pans which have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done. Stack layers with unsweetened and spiced applesauce. Makes 6 to 8 layers.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and de-stem mushrooms. Stuff the mushrooms with a mixture of mayonnaise, bread crumbs and Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Broil the mushrooms 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry rhubarb marmalade
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil and boil for 20 minutes. Add Jell-O.
Pour into jars and seal while hot.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal(or mel's morsels)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend together sugars and shortening. Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts.
Spray cookie sheets with cooking spray and drop dough by teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 dozen.
Can be doubled or cut in half easily.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Then add apples, nuts and raisins.
In another bowl, mix flour, salt, soda and cinnamon, then add to wet mixture.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and cube potatoes; boil until potatoes are tender.
Drain and put in casserole dish.
Stir in margarine and soup; add onions and ham or bacon bits.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly hot and cheese is slightly brown.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Mix vanilla pudding mixes and milk.
Let stand a few minutes.
Mix frozen whipped topping into pudding mix, then add cream cheese and powdered sugar to pudding mix.
Crush the package of Oreo cookies in blender or with rolling pin.
In a flower pot or large plastic sand bucket, layer the crushed cookies over the pudding mix.
May add gummy worms and artificial flowers!

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Beat eggs.
Add vinegar and sugar; heat and beat constantly until mixture thickens.
Add 2 tablespoons butter; let cool.
Mix in bowl the grapes, chunky pineapple, fruit cocktail, nuts and marshmallows.
Add cooked, cooled mixture; fold in the whipped cream.
You can add coconut and raisins if you wish.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Add margarine and bring to rolling boil.
Dump all flour at once into boiling water.
Lower heat and stir vigorously until ball of dough forms.
Remove from heat. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Continue stirring until smooth, thick batter forms.
Drop dough on ungreased cookie sheet by tablespoonfuls (generous).
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and fill with sweetened whipping cream, whipped.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat undiluted mushroom soup.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water; mix with soup.
Add cream cheese and blend well.
Add shrimp, celery, green onions and mayonnaise.
Place in salad mold and refrigerate overnight.
Unmold and serve with crackers.
Crab may be substituted for shrimp.

title: quick spoon rolls
directions: Mix sugar and melted butter; add warm water.
Sprinkle yeast over mixture and stir together, then add flour; mix by hand.
Dip spoonfuls out in muffin pan sprayed with Pam.

title: aunt sarah's  coconut delight
directions: First Layer:
Beat cream cheese, one cup of cool whip, and one cup of powdered sugar until smoothed.
Spread on to crust. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: marinated carrots "copper penny salad"
directions: Peel and slice thinly the carrots.
Cook and drain.
Add onion and bell pepper, sliced or chopped.
Set aside.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix cooked, mashed sweet potatoes with mixer.
Add sugars, butter, milk and eggs.
Add vanilla and spices.
Mix well and spoon into 3 (9-inch) pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 3 pies.

title: shrimp and mushrooms pasta
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside. Cook pasta according to package; drain and set aside.

title: holiday breakfast bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat eggs and oil; add to flour mixture.
Add pecans, coconut, bananas, pineapple and vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour to 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: baked zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add sugar, salt and basil.
Beat egg; add milk, pepper and crackers. Mix together with squash.
Cook 15 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with Parmesan or other cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: german schnitzel wiener
directions: Choose veal or pork cutlet.
Schnitzel should be lightly pounded with flat surface, to tenderize.
Sprinkle each schnitzel with salt.
Dredge in flour.
Tap off excess.
Dip in beaten egg and fine, dry bread or cracker crumbs.
Make sure each schnitzel has a complete coat of crumbs to retain juices while cooking. Pan-fry schnitzel slowly in butter or margarine over low heat until golden brown.

title: tomato chili sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in large kettle.
Cook until real thick.

title: walkabout soup
directions: Heat water to boiling and add bouillon cubes. Boil till dissolved and remove from heat.
Cut onions into thin slices and add to broth. Add salt and pepper.
Return to heat and bring mixture back to boiling and then turn heat to low and simmer uncovered for 1 hour. While stirring, sift flour into soup. Simmer for an additional 30 minutes.
Add cream and 1 cup of shredded cheddar.
Simmer for 10 more minutes.
Serve hot and top with a little Cheddar and Monterey Jack.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Heat whipping cream in a double boiler.
Add egg yolks, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Add 3/4 of the whipped cream, pineapple and cherries.
Be sure to drain the fruit. Add halved marshmallows.
Let stand for 24 hours before serving. Enjoy!

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients quickly.
Put in pie shell and bake in 350° oven until firm; about 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.
This pie has a custard texture.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: In a small bowl, beat the cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic powder and red pepper.
Spread evenly in pie plate.
Spread pizza sauce over the top.
Sprinkle pepperoni, onion and green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese; bake 5 minutes more, or until cheese is melted.

title: easy salisbury steak
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and form into oblong patties. Brown in shortening; drain.
Add the mushroom gravy and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Melt butter in a 3-quart pan.
Blend in flour and stir until smooth.
Slowly stir in chicken broth.
Add pepper and Old Bay and simmer for 2 minutes.
Slowly add milk.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Do not boil.
Add crabmeat and salt to taste.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Chop shrimp into medium small pieces.
Chop eggs.
Mix together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise to make creamy.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Combine sugars and shortening.
Mix well.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and stir into first mixture.
Add vanilla, oatmeal, dry cereal, coconut and raisins, stirring after each addition.
Form into 1-inch balls; place on lightly greased cookie sheet; to flatten the balls, use a glass tumbler, greased lightly on the bottom or dusted with flour.
Or, drop the batter from a teaspoon, well apart, on a lightly greased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove immediately to rack to cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate all of the cheese.
Combine with Bisquick and sausage. Mix altogether (works best by hand).
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender on high speed and count to 10 slowly.
Pour into well-greased pie plate (9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs well in a bowl; add bananas and mash well.
Add sugar, flour (sifted) and soda and additional ingredients if desired.
Mix well and bake in a loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: condensed milk lemon pie
directions: Put condensed milk in large mixing bowl.
In small mixing bowl, whip cream until soft peaks from.
Combine the lemon juice, vanilla flavoring and food coloring to the condensed milk.
Stir until thick.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Pour into graham cracker pie shells.
Makes 2 (8 or 9-inch) pies.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown meat and onions; add taco seasoning mix.
Mix corn meal, corn, eggs and milk.
Spread a layer of bread mixture on bottom of pan, layer of meat and cheese.
Pour rest of corn bread on top of meat mixture.
Grease pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: orange pineapple punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine pineapple, milk and orange juice. Just before serving, add ginger ale, stir and then scoop in scoops of orange sherbet.

title: nut chewies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: french meat pie
directions: Cook onions in oil until soft; add all other ingredients except potatoes and completely cover with water.
Cook until meat is brown.
After potatoes are cooked, mash them slightly (should be in small pieces).
Add potatoes to meat mixture and skim most of liquid.
Put in crust and bake until crust is golden brown.
To make 2 pies, bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients for crust.
Cream powdered sugar, eggs, oleo and vanilla together until fluffy.
Spread over crust. Slice bananas over filling.
Add pineapple on top of bananas.
Put strawberries on, then Cool Whip on top of strawberries.
Top with pecans and cherries.
Drizzle chocolate over that.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat the rolls into 2 (9 x 12-inch) pans.
Bake according to directions on package.
Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese and Hidden Valley.
Spread on baked rolls.
Arrange vegetables on top. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.

title: chicken in a basket
directions: Place beef on top of chicken pieces and roll.
Put toothpick through center to hold it together.
Place all chicken, once it has been rolled, in casserole dish.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of celery soup and sour cream together.
Pour over the chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: carrot bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and carrots all together. Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Bake in a large cookie sheet (greased) in a 325° oven.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Boil noodles until soft.
Drain and rinse.
Add cheeses and wine, mixing until blended.
Add cream, fish and
crab meat or other fish and blend well.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Stir pudding into Cool Whip.
Add pineapple (with the juice) and marshmallows.
Add walnuts or pistachio nuts (optional).
Fold together and let stand 12 hours.

title: little richie's fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butter; add egg and then sugar and vanilla. Mix well; put in a buttered dish.
Let cool.

title: hot chicken sandwich
directions: Cut crusts from 12 slices of bread; butter.
Make filling with the first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Place half the slices in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Fill with sandwich mix and cover with second slice. Mix sour cream and soup.
Spread over sandwiches.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and bring to a boil.
Will cook 3 chickens on the grill.
Keep sauce hot while cooking chicken.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Melt 3/4 stick butter.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add egg, buttermilk, vanilla, melted butter and grated orange peel.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill 12 well buttered muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: rice with mushrooms
directions: Melt butter.
Add uncooked rice and saute.
Add sliced mushrooms and dry onion soup mix.
Add 1 cup water.
Cover and cook 25 minutes over low heat.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Use a whole young chicken.
Boil until tender.
Peel from bone and dice meat, not skin.
Use only enough oil to fry corn tortilla on both sides (about 15 seconds).
In each tortilla, put chicken, onion and cilantro (optional) and then roll.
After all tortillas have been placed in a baking pan, pour enchilada sauce on top. Sprinkle cheese and olives evenly on top.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add alternately with buttermilk.
Mix both mixtures together. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: sour cream mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Cream 2 cheeses together.
Add to potatoes.
Mix. Pour into buttered baking pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Great for family get-togethers.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Blend all ingredients by hand until well mixed.
Pour into lightly buttered quiche pan or 9-inch deep dish pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until top is lightly browned and center is set.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: golden cheese souffle
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Grease casserole.
Pour mixture over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Put in dish of water and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice according to directions (can cook broccoli not quite done).
Combine all ingredients.
Put margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Early in the morning, mix sugar, water, Kool-Aid and pineapple juice.
Mix well in big pitcher and put in icebox.
(Cool for 8 to 12 hours.)
When ready to use, pour ginger ale and mixture together and serve.

title: italian wontons
directions: Saute Italian sausage and chopped green onion until onion is tender and meat is browned.
Cool; combine with chopped parsley and grated cheese.
Spoon small amounts onto single wontons. Dampen edges of wontons and fold into triangles.
Join 45° angle corners and pinch together.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Serve hot, dipping into Italian sauce.

title: squeeze butter
directions: Cut up block of butter.
Then put it in empty bottle.
Next put in microwave for 2 minutes.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Debone chicken breasts.
Wrap each piece with bacon.
Cover bottom of pan with chipped beef.
Arrange breasts on beef.
Mix soups and mushrooms.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup slivered almonds on top.
Bake uncovered for 4 hours at 250°.

title: cauliflower-pea salad
directions: Break up cauliflower into small flowerets.
Mix with peas, onion and mushrooms.
Combine oil, lemon juice, salt and mustard. Pour over top and mix together.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in their	jackets
in boiling water until nearly tender;
drain.
Cut
in
1/2-inch	slices.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Cook together sugar, water and margarine in another pan for a few
minutes.
Then
stir
in lemon juice and pour over potatoes.
Bake at	375°
for
20 to 25 minutes, basting with syrup.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: For cake mix shortening and sugar; cream.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites and add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in round cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken wings
directions: Wash chicken wings and pat dry.
In a bowl, combine cracker or bread crumbs, herbs and Parmesan cheese.
Add seasonings and mix well to blend.
Dip chicken into melted butter, then into crumb coating.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until brown and tender.

title: scottish trifle
directions: Make 1 or 2 packages vanilla pudding and layer in order given: preserves to cover bottom of dish, cake broken into pieces, half of vanilla pudding, drained fruit cocktail, half of vanilla pudding, cover with whipped cream, garnish with sliced banana and strawberries.
Make in early a.m. or let set overnight. Serves 6 to 8.

title: nippy nachos
directions: Arrange chips on large waxed paper lined glass plate. Sprinkle sauce over chips, then sprinkle cheese over chips evenly. Top each chip with olive.
Microwave on High for 1 minute. Rotate dish and microwave 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: curry chicken(philippino style)
directions: Cook garlic and onions in hot cooking oil.
When starting to look transparent, add the chicken.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes. Then add 3 tablespoons of coconut milk; stir well.
Cover and cook for another 10 minutes.
Then add the remaining coconut milk, okra, season with salt and pepper or Season-All.
Again cover and cook for 40 minutes in a medium heat.
Serve hot with rice.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together until blended.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until set.
This can be put in an unbaked pie shell or into a pie plate without a shell.
If potatoes are too sweet, 1 cup of sugar might be enough.

title: spinach rye dip
directions: Cook spinach and onion and drain well.
Mix ingredients and put in hollow of round rye loaf.
Use broken rye bread to dip into spinach dip.

title: spanish rice(vegetarian)
directions: In large skillet, saute onion in oil until soft.
Add garlic, peppers, celery, bay leaves, spices, salt and pepper.
Saute 3 to 4 minutes.
Add tomato puree and rice.
Cover and cook over low heat until warmed through.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put hash browns over melted margarine.
(Lightly salt hash browns, if desired.)
Mix together soup, sour cream, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Spread over hash browns.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and combine with corn flake crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken; save broth.
Take chicken off the bone.
Dice potatoes, onions and tomatoes.
Cook in broth until potatoes are done.
Add chicken, sauce, corn and season to taste.

title: oven potatoes and onions
directions: Cut potatoes into large chunks.
Put in plastic bag and add onion soup mix and oil.
Shake well.
Pour into shallow baking dish and bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: marcine's graham cracker heath bars
directions: Place graham crackers on a cookie sheet, enough to fill the pan and have them touching.
Mix butter and margarine; add sugar and boil exactly 2 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake 12 minutes in 325° preheated oven.
Remove from pan immediately.
Put crackers on a stack of newspapers to help them cool.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add all other ingredients and simmer. Garnish with chopped avocado, sour cream, shredded cheese, corn chips or olives when dished into bowls. Enjoy.

title: tourtieres
directions: Cook on top of stove for 1 1/2 hours.
Just cover with water. The cloves should be in a small bag.
Let entire mixture cool off. When cool, place in a pie crust shell and cook in the oven for 1/2 hour at 400°.
A French-Canadian recipe.
Makes 4 pies.
Bon Appetit!

title: cheese-pineapple salad
directions: Heat pineapple.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Soak gelatin in cold water for 10 minutes.
Add to hot mixture.
Put in icebox; when cool and when it begins to set, add cheese and whipped cream and then chill.

title: momma linda's "graham cracker cake"
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour two 8-inch round cake pans.

Beat shortening and sugar together until creamy. Beat egg yolks until light and add to sugar mixture. In separate bowl, mix baking powder with cracker crumbs, salt and nuts. Add cracker mixture to sugar mixture, alternating with milk. Beat egg whites and add to mixture. Pour into pans and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: company breakfast
directions: Slice the pork sausage and combine with the remaining ingredients.
Put n a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Microwave on Medium for 16 minutes. Serve right away.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Partially cook broccoli as directed.
Saute onions and celery in a small amount of butter. Gently add this to the rest of the recipe.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°, until set.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and bring to a boil; boil 12 minutes, stirring constantly.
Combine all the other ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour hot mixture over them and stir until melted. Pour in ungreased pans.
Cool slightly, then cut into squares.
Do not refrigerate.
Yields 5 pounds.

title: red cabbage with apples
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion in butter until tender but not brown.
Add the cabbage, salt, pepper, brown sugar, cider, vinegar and apples.
Cover and simmer until the cabbage and apples are tender and the liquid is reduced, about 1 hour.
Sprinkle with bacon and parsley.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Pare eggplant and cut in 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook in salt water until tender and almost dry.

title: green bean creole
directions: Put 1 tablespoon bacon grease, margarine or salad oil in pan with green pepper, celery and onion. Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper. Add green beans and heat thoroughly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix soup and water in a baking dish.
Stir in uncooked rice. Lay chicken on top of the rice.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: classical chicken
directions: Brown chicken in frying pan.
Using 2 crescent rolls (should be shaped in a rectangle), roll each piece of chicken and place in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish sprayed with Pam.
Pour cream of mushroom soup and mushrooms on top of chicken.
Spread out.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour covered with foil.

title: candy turtles
directions: Melt caramel kisses in milk over low heat, stirring constantly.
When completely melted, add pecans and mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
(If candy sticks to fingers, dip finger in cup of cool water occasionally.) Let cool until firm. Melt candiquick in its own container according to directions on package.
Dip each piece of candy into the chocolate and back on wax paper.
Let cool until firm.

title: 15 minute stroganoff
directions: Cut meat diagonally across grain in very thin strips.
Brown meat in melted margarine.
Add 2/3 cup water and mushrooms.
Stir in soup mix; heat to boiling.
Blend sour cream and flour; add to mixture.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens. Sauce will be thin.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.
Serves 5.

title: sauerbraten venison or beef
directions: Rub meat with the cut surface of garlic, salt and pepper. Place in large pan and heat vinegar, water, onions, bay leaves, peppercorns and sugar together, but don't boil.
Pour hot mixture over meat, cover and refrigerate for 4 to 8 days, turning meat each day.

title: fruit punch
directions: Pour over large cake of ice.
Serves 12.

title: pear bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Mix in buttermilk, then flour and other dry ingredients.
Fold in pears and vanilla.
Pour batter into four greased 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: candied grapefruit peel
directions: Cut grapefruit into large wedges and remove peel.
Cut the peel into long strips about 1/4-inch wide.
Put in a heavy saucepan and cover with boiling water.
Cook at rolling boil for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Repeat this boiling process 3 times.
Drain and set aside.
In the same saucepan, combine 3 cups sugar and 2 cups water.
Place over high heat and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil.
Add the drained peels.
Stir and reduce heat to a gentle boil.
Cover partially, stirring occasionally, for an hour or until most liquid has been absorbed and peel is transparent.
Remove from heat.
Cover a large work area with wax paper.
Pour a cup of remaining sugar on wax paper. Roll the candied peel in sugar.
Shake off excess sugar and set on side to dry for 2 hours.
Store in airtight containers or jars.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, oil and half of flour.
Mix in remaining flour to make a stiff dough. Beat 20 strokes.
Spread on pizza pan.
Let rise in warm place for 10 minutes.
Cook for 7 minutes at 375°.
Put on toppings.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and browned.

title: steak casserole
directions: Combine soups in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into bottom of crock-pot.
Add 1 cup rice.
Place cut up meat next.
Pour the rest of the soup over meat.
Add butter and cook for 2 hours on high, then on low for 3 to 4 hours.
You can cook on low for 8 hours.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and add celery, onion and bell pepper.
Pour in large pan, 9 x 12-inch.
Add 4 1/2 cups boiling water and remaining ingredients, mix well.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: hash browns quiche
directions: Press hash browns into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Saute onion in butter, then mix with cheeses and ham.
Spread over potatoes.
Combine butter and milk.
Pour over the cheese and ham mixture.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes more.

title: pound cakegroves, texas
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, flour, egg, flour, egg, flour till you've reached 6 eggs and 2 c. flour.
Grease and flour bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper.
(You can spray with Pam to avoid the extra fat grams from using margarine.) Add this to tomatoes and red pepper.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Thicken and sweeten mixture.
Add shrimp.
Serve over rice.
Some like to add a little Tabasco sauce to make it hot.

title: white christmas punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add evaporated milk and almond extract; let cool.
Chill until ready to serve.
Combine milk mixture and remaining ingredients in punch bowl just before serving, stirring to break ice cream into small pieces.
Makes approximately 25 (8 ounces each) servings.

title: baked crab supreme
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour slowly.
Add cream and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Mix salt and pepper to taste and sherry.
Remove from heat and add crab meat.
Pour mixture into a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 400° until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: lemon snowballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar and egg until well blended.
Add lemon juice and peel.
Combine flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Add almonds. Cover and refrigerate the dough for at least 1 hour or overnight. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned (cookies will not brown on top).
Remove immediately to wire rack; cool for 5 minutes, then roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: "killer" brownies
directions: In large mixing bowl, thoroughly blend brownie mix, water, oil, eggs and nuts.
Grease the bottom only (or spray with Pam) of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Baking 45 minutes will result in "gooey" brownie squares and 55 minutes makes brownies more cake-like. Experiment to desired doneness.
Spread the top of the brownies with 1/2 can of frosting immediately after removing from oven.

title: upside down cake
directions: Mix well and pour over any fruit mixed with sugar and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients; mix with egg mixture.
Add carrots and nuts.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: peaches and sweet potatoes
directions: Drain peaches and potatoes and set aside.
Boil these juices with sugar and oleo (to taste) and pour over fruit and potatoes. Bake at 325°.

title: marian o'brien frosting
directions: Cream butter and Crisco; add sugar and flour.
Beat well. Turn mixer down and slowly add milk and vanilla.
Beat vigorously for several minutes.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Return to oven and bake about 20 minutes more.

title: tuna pate
directions: Drain tuna; add cream cheese.
Mix in rest of ingredients. Work with hands until completely combined.
Shape into fish or ball.
Place on serving dish.
Serve with crackers.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Mix with spoon.
Put chocolate chips in last.
Mix easy so they won't all go to the bottom.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: white marshmallow icing
directions: Combine
sugar,
egg whites and water in double boiler. Beat with electric or rotary beaters over boiling water until soft peaks
form.
Add
marshmallow
cream.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Remove from heat.
Beat in vanilla.

title: greek salad
directions: Make a sauce of olive oil, lemon juice, mayonnaise and Greek seasoning. Chill. Mix all remaining ingredients. Pour sauce on. Toss, chill and serve.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and peanuts in pan.
Bring to a boil and cook to hard crack stage (290°), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat to stir in baking soda.
Pour into greased cooking sheet and pull and stretch thin.
Yields one pound.

title: gladys osgood cole's uncooked cookies
directions: Stir together oats, coconut and nuts.
Set aside.
Boil together for 3 minutes the remaining ingredients.
Pour over the oat mixture.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Heat cranberry sauce in a pan. Stir in dry jello. When sauce is almost smooth, add the pineapple and nuts. Refrigerate.

title: caramel cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, oleo, 1/2 box powdered sugar and milk.
Bring to rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining powdered sugar and vanilla.
Stir until thick enough to spread.
If it gets too thick, add 1 teaspoon of water.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes until done.
Ice and sprinkle with choice of nuts.

title: bean soup
directions: Rinse dried mixed beans.
Place in large Dutch oven pan and sprinkle salt on beans.
Cover beans with 2 quarts water.
Soak overnight.

title: whoopie pie cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, milk, egg and salt together.
Blend in the remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonful onto a greased cookie sheet and bake in a 425° oven for about 7 minutes.
Let cool.

title: party pork chops
directions: Brown chops in shortening in a heavy skillet.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Place an onion slice and pepper ring on each chop.
Pour soup over all.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour at 325°.

title: n.w. cioppino(fish stew)
directions: Cut fish fillets into 1-inch pieces.
In 3 1/2 or 4-quart saucepan heat oil; add onions, green pepper, carrots, celery and garlic.
Saute and stir frequently until vegetables are tender, about 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except fish, and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer until flavors are blended, about 20 minutes.
Stir in fish and cook until fish flakes easily when tested with fork, 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: vanishing oatmeal bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat together margarine or butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; add to liquid mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and raisins; mix well.
Bake 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking pan.
Yield: 24 medium bars.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley and noodles.
Simmer 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf.
Add noodles and parsley.
Cook 10 minutes or longer until noodles are tender.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter, milk and salt at a full boil for 5 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in the chocolate chips, vanilla and walnuts.
Stir rapidly until melted, then stir in the marshmallow cream.
Pour in buttered pan.
Chill. Cut in squares.
Big batch!!!

title: delicious chicken rolls
directions: Pound chicken to 1/2-inch thickness.
Spoon 1 teaspoon cream cheese with chives into each piece of chicken.
Roll chicken and wrap with 1 piece of bacon.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Then place under broiler for 5 minutes.
Turn once to crisp bacon.

title: cajun pork roast
directions: Rub surface of roast lightly with cooking oil.
Combine seasoning mixture and rub over all surfaces of roast.
Place roast in shallow pan and roast at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: pollo con salsiccia(chicken with sausage)
directions: Put olive oil in pan with first 3 ingredients; saut.
Remove from heat.
Add sausage and set aside.
Coat chicken with flour and pepper.
Brown in large pan and remove excess oil.
Slowly add 4 cups of chicken broth and sausage mixture.
Simmer until chicken and sausage are cooked.
Add additional broth as needed.
Season with ground peppercorns to taste.
During last 5 to 10 minutes of cooking, add white wine and balsamic vinegar.
Serve over pasta and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: tomato and onion salad
directions: Mix well and chill for at least 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla and mix well. Add dry ingredients and mix.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peach crisp
directions: Drain peaches and layer into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine flour, brown sugar, oatmeal and butter.
Mix until crumbly and spread over the peaches.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Separate rolls into rectangles.
Spread uncooked sausage over whole rectangle.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Roll up.
Slice into sections and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: flo's lemon chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Place oil in skillet and brown chicken.
Mash garlic with salt and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour this mixture over the brown chicken. Cover and cook at 325° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: praline squares
directions: Melt the shortening over low heat.
Remove and add brown sugar.
Let cool.
Stir in egg and remaining ingredients.
Spread in a greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream sugar and add 1 1/2 cups sugar gradually.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Blend in melted chocolate.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together by sifting.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk to already creamed mixture.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff enough to hold point, then add remaining sugar.
Fold into batter.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven. Cake must not be overcooked.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Bring 2 cups of water to boiling.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Add other ingredients. Mix together.
Chill.
Serve with meats or casseroles.

title: rich and easy chocolate topping
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in small saucepan; blend in milk.
Add margarine and salt.
Cook and stir constantly until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream or other desserts.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: luscious lime pie
directions: Mix pie filling, Jell-O, sugar, water and eggs.
Cook until thickened over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip and mix thoroughly.
Pour into crust and top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: jalapeno sweet pickles
directions: Put all in stainless container and stir every day for 3 days. (Or put back into original container.)
Shake well each day. Keep refrigerated and put into smaller containers as needed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil
chicken and debone.
Crush 1 tube of crackers and put in
bottom
of
casserole
dish.
Pour
3/4 of the melted butter and make a crust.
Add chicken on crust.
Mix soups and sour cream
and pour over chicken.
Crush and put 1/2 tube of crackers on chicken soups and rest of melted butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken and olives ala olsen
directions: Combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken.
Brown in butter.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Mix together all but egg whites.
Beat egg whites (not too dry).
Fold into mixture.
Stir well, so spices will not settle to bottom.
Pour into 2 pie crusts and bake until nicely browned at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: micro-chops
directions: Trim fat off pork chops.
Slice the potatoes into long microsafe dish.
Arrange pork chops over potatoes.
Combine soups and pour over chops and potatoes.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes, turning chops and dish once after 2 minutes. Keep covered.
Microwave on Medium setting 12 to 15 minutes or until tender and no pink remains.
Remove chops to serving dish, pouring soup mix over all or serve in separate dish.

title: snowballs
directions: Sift together flour and salt; set aside.
Combine butter, sugar, vanilla and egg; mix well.
Add flour mixture, nuts and chocolate chips.
Form into small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a 350° oven for approximately 9 minutes.
After the cookies are cool, roll them in powdered sugar.

title: strawberry or raspberry pie
directions: Cook
sugar, water, cornstarch and Karo until clear and add jello.
Pour over berries in a baked pie shell.

title: lo-cal chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, honey and Rice Krispies; pour in pie pan. Use a greased cup to press crust.
Slice 1 banana and place them on the crust.
Mix chocolate pudding according to directions and pour over bananas and crust.
Refrigerate 1 hour until set.
Top with chocolate Cool Whip.

title: meat and vegetable casserole
directions: Boil macaroni.
Brown ground meat and onions.
Add all ingredients except cheese to ground meat and cook for 15 minutes. Add cheese and cook until melted.
Can be cooked on stove as directed or baked in oven in a casserole dish at 350° for 20 minutes.
Different vegetables can be added or substituted.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cook celery and onion in water until tender.
Meanwhile, combine remaining dry ingredients (store separately, if dressing is to be baked later).
Just before baking, add celery and onion, plus the liquid to the dry mix.
This should be moist, but compact.
If dry, add a little more liquid.
Combine well.
Bake in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, in a hot oven, 400°, for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
I use this to stuff turkey.

title: congealed salad
directions: Bring the pie filling and sugar to a boil. Take off the stove. Mix the jello and add it to the pie filling/sugar mixture.
Add the crushed pineapple.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: cherry or pineapple yum yum
directions: Mix crumbs with melted butter.
Place in a dish, reserving a few for the topping.
Beat Dream Whip with milk.
When almost stiff, add sugar and cream cheese.
Beat until stiff.
Pour half mixture over crumbs, then add pineapple.
Top with remaining mixture and sprinkle with reserved crumbs. Chill several hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken (save 2 cups broth). Bone chicken and spread in 13 x 9-inch dish. Sprinkle dressing mix over chicken. Mix 2 cups broth, butter and soup. Bring to a boil; pour over chicken. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese.
Add remaining milk and chocolate mixture and beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping, blending until smooth. Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Garnish.
Let stand at room temperature to soften before serving.

title: ribs and potatoes
directions: Cook ribs for about 1 1/2 hours, then put in cabbage and cook about 1/2 hour.
Put in potatoes and cook until done.

title: custard bread pudding
directions: Let bread stand uncovered overnight to dry.
Cover raisins with boiling water, let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix eggs, milk, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla or rosewater.
