Place raisins in ungreased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over. Spread bread slices with butter.
Cut each slice diagonally into 4 triangles.
Place atop egg mixture, buttered side up.
Sprinkle with mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and nutmeg.
Set baking dish in pan on oven rack.
Pour hot water into pan to depth of 1 inch. Bake at 350° until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: butterscotch apple-pecan cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl combine butterscotch morsels, brown sugar, flour and cinnamon; set aside.
Place apples in 13 x 9-inch pan; sprinkle morsels mixture over apples.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Trim tough stems from okra pods, but do not cut into seed. Pack in clean sterile jars.
Add 1 tablespoon dill seed and 1 clove of garlic to each jar.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Melt in top of double boiler.
Cover each ball good.
Lift out with toothpick.
Place on waxed paper and chill.

title: pull buns
directions: Combine sugar, salt and butter; add to milk.
Add yeast and eggs.
Add flour to make stiff batter.
Let rise.
Stir down and let rise again.
Pinch off in balls, dip in melted butter, then cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Pile loosely in angel food pan or loaf pans.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove excess fat from chicken.
Place chicken, meaty side up, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients, except apricots; brush over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, brushing with soy mixture occasionally 60 to 70 minutes.
About 5 minutes before chicken is done, arrange apricots around chicken. Brush with soy mixture.
Bake 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in a large bowl in the microwave.
Chop onion and two bags of the beef in a food processor.
Stir onion and beef mixture in with cream cheese and spices.
Mix well and either form into a ball or put in a bowl.
(If you choose to form into a ball, place ball in the refrigerator to chill.)
Chop remaining bag of beef in food processor.
If forming into a ball take out of refrigerator after chilled and roll in the chopped beef until covered.
If you chose to place in bowl just sprinkle the last bag of beef on top.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix 3/4 salsa with cream cheese, using mixer.
Spread in a glass dish.
On top of spread, add cheeses, shredded lettuce and remaining salsa.
Garnish with olives, if desired.
Place nacho chips around the edges of the dish.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook first 7 ingredients until tender.
Thicken with flour and milk.
Add chopped hard-boiled eggs.
Add 1 or 2 cups milk to make more.

title: belle luther's coconut cream cake
directions: Grate a fresh coconut; whip one pint whipping cream, add 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
In between each layer, spread whipping cream mixture and top with coconut.
Cover top and sides with cream and coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: gingerbread crackers
directions: Mix ingredients and add enough plain flour to roll soft dough on.
Cut and bake in hot oven.

title: shasta shake(nonfat)
directions: In blender, add crushed ice, frozen blueberries or any other berries, powdered milk, syrup and Shasta.
Blend until frothy. Makes 2 servings.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate, peanut butter and butter.
Pour over cereal. Put confectioners sugar in a brown grocery bag.
Add cereal and mix.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in bowl and chill at least 2 hours.

title: cheese and sausage dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot and serve warm.

title: portuguese tuna
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add onions, garlic, green pepper, celery and parsley; saute until tender.
Blend in tomato sauce, water, bay leaf, orange peel, cumin, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Discard orange peel and bay leaf.
Serve over rice or use to fill warm flour tortillas.

title: hot cinnamon-orange cider
directions: Combine cider and 1 stick cinnamon in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Discard cinnamon stick.

title: angel hash salad
directions: Combine the cornstarch and sugar.
Add the pineapple juice and egg yolks; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
When mixture starts to boil on sides, lower heat.
Fold in the whipped cream, then fold in the pineapple tidbits and marshmallows.
Chill overnight.
Just before serving, add the sliced bananas.
Mix well.

title: old fashioned sweet bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and Crisco.
Add flour until thick (like cake batter), then add flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cook in a warm iron skillet.
Best when served warm.

title: mushroom chicken quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix rice, 2 of the egg whites and 1/4 teaspoon rosemary.
Press onto the bottom and sides of lightly greased 10-inch quiche dish or pie plate for crust.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs with oil until foamy.
Add sugar and water.
Add flour and cinnamon.
Batter will be thick.	 Add apples and nuts. Spread into a 9x13 pan and bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Combine noodles, butter, orange juice, 1/2 sugar and eggs in large bowl; mix well.
Stir in raisins, salt and pie filling. Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix cornflakes, 3 tablespoons sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice in bowl.
Sprinkle over pudding.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zesty pork chops
directions: Season chops with salt.
Brown in hot shortening; drain.

title: low-fat vanilla pudding
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine milk, yogurt, pudding mix and vanilla.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Spoon into serving dish.
Chill. Yields 6 servings.

title: cherry pie congealed salad
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients.
Fold in milk mixture with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: a berry good banana smoothie
directions: Blend together in a blender.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange layers of bread, cooked sausage, cheese and mushrooms.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° covered for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix all together with a mixer. Serve with Fritos.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve immediately.

title: biscuit snacks
directions: Mix pork and beans, hot dogs, barbecue sauce, brown sugar and onion all together.
Set off to side and put biscuits in muffin tins.
Make a big dent in the middle of each.
Pour your mixture in the dent.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes on 425°.
Take out and sprinkle with cheese.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan.	In large bowl cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and blend in bananas, milk and vanilla.
In small bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Add to creamed mixture and mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.	Cool 5 minutes.
Wrap and store in refrigerator.

title: afternoon cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Set to one side.

title: sausage and cheese quiche
directions: Fry sausage and drain. Sprinkle into crust. Combine remaining ingredients and gently pour over cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix flour, sugar, milk, salt and baking powder to form batter.
Pour over melted butter.
Spread fruit filling of your choice over batter.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: seafood creole
directions: Prepare roux by heating oil or margarine in a large skillet and blending in flour over medium heat.
Stir constantly until brown, being careful not to scorch.
Add water gradually and cook until thick and smooth.
Add remaining ingredients except rice. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaves and serve over hot rice.

title: golden cheese potatoes
directions: Melt butter in dish in oven.
Shake potatoes in mixture. Season and bake in butter at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tex-mex tortilla appetizers
directions: Combine cream cheese, green chilies, green onions, black olives, Cheddar cheese and garlic salt in a bowl.
Spread a heaping tablespoon (or more if you like) of cream cheese mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up the tortilla in jellyroll fashion. Place seam side down on a baking sheet.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Slice each tortilla into 4 pieces and serve with picante sauce on the side for dipping.
This recipe makes about 4 dozen.

title: great canned string beans
directions: Drain and rinse string beans (this is important).
Replace liquid with fresh water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Season.
Cook on low heat about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk, margarine and salt in skillet and cook at a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and cool until firm.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, pineapple, peppers, onions and salt and freeze. Roll into nuts and serve.

title: yavonne's yuletide mixer
directions: Mix the ingredients together in a large saucepan; simmer 3 hours.
The mixture will be water consistency at first, but will thicken after 3 hours.
Serve warm, so keep over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Serves 24 people.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine, sugar and cocoa over low heat.
Stir to keep from scorching.
Add milk, flavoring and eggs.
Do not boil mixture.
Stir in coconut, nuts and salt.
Cool slightly before pouring into crust.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until pie is thickened.
This pie can be frozen.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package using 2 round cake pans.
Cool.

title: oven stroganoff
directions: Cook meat in 1 tablespoon butter until it loses its red color. Add onions.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Place into casserole.
Melt remaining butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Add bouillon cubes, hot water, salt, pepper, mustard, Worcestershire and ketchup.
Cook until thick.
Beat in sour cream.
Pour mixture over meat.
Cool; cover and refrigerate.
The day of dinner:
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple-pecan loaf
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Alternately add dry ingredients and orange concentrate to creamed mixture, stirring after each addition.
Stir in undrained pineapple and pecans.
Turn into well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched (or use toothpick test).

title: one bowl chocolate fudge(microwave)
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large microwave bowl on High 2 to 3 minutes, until chocolate is melted.
Stir after 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir until all chocolate is melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: squash dressing
directions: Put ingredients in large pot.
Cook over low heat until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf and add 2 cups cornbread crumbs, 2 beaten eggs and enough chicken broth to make soft mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Grate 1/2 cup cheese on top and bake 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Combine flour, salt and paprika.
Coat chicken; brown in butter.
Add water; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Save pan drippings.
Arrange chicken in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch bake dish.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup half and half.
Stir into pan drippings. Over low heat, stir in remaining half and half, lemon juice, onion, lemon peel and ginger.
Cook until thickened; pour over chicken.
Cover; bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with cheese; return to oven until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Combine cole slaw with uncooked noodles (reserve seasoning package) and almonds. Cover and chill. Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, pepper and seasoning. Shake or stir well. Cover and chill. Mix together prior to serving.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain and rinse sauerkraut very well several minutes.
Put in a large bowl.
Add all other ingredients.
Pack in jars.
Let stand in refrigerator for two days before serving.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients except crushed corn flakes.
Spoon into 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with crushed corn flakes.
Bake 55 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: "company's best" pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with boiling water.
Allow to stand until the next morning.
Drain.
Repeat this procedure on next 3 mornings. On the 5th day, drain and slice cucumbers in 1/2-inch slices or pieces.
Combine sugar, spices, salt and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand (covered) for 2 days.
On 3rd day, bring to boiling, then seal in hot, sterilized jars.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots until soft; drain and cool. Combine all other ingredients and marinate carrots for 12 hours.

title: midnight chocolate cake
directions: Blend shortening and sugar until creamy; add eggs.
Then put cocoa in hot water and add to shortening, sugar and egg mixture. Then add flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Blend well.
Add vanilla and blend.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Place in greased square pan.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix egg, buttermilk and baking soda well.
Then add flour, sugar, Crisco and baking powder; mix well.
Brown on lightly greased griddle.
Turn pancakes only once when bubbles appear.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except hash browns, corn flakes and 1/2 cube butter.
When mixed real well, add hash browns and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crumbled corn flakes and the 1/2 cube butter (melted and poured over corn flakes).
Spread cheese on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream(1 gallon)
directions: Mix all ingredients above and pour into ice cream freezer container.
Use directions for freezing.

title: pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, cheese and 2/3 cup cracker crumbs.
Mix flour with sugar and add to pineapple mixture.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Last 5 to 7 minutes of cooking time, put 1/3 cup cracker crumbs on top.
Finish baking.

title: lemon jelly cake
directions: Mix according to package directions and bake in 3 layers. Cool and fill with Lemon Jelly Filling.

title: glazed baked sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in water to cover in saucepan for 15 minutes or until nearly tender.
Drain; halve potatoes lengthwise. Arrange in greased baking dish.
Mix 3 tablespoons boiling water, brown sugar, butter and salt in saucepan; cook for 3 minutes. Pour over potatoes; top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: papaya ring mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot papaya nectar.
Add lemon juice.
Chill until syrupy.
Add drained mandarin orange sections and grapes. Fold in sour cream.
Pour into mold.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: date fingers
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine.
Beat in sugar, egg and vanilla. Stir in dates and nuts.
Bring slowly to a boil.
Cook on low heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in Rice Krispies.
Cool and shape into small rolls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: puppy chow
directions: In microwave, melt chocolate chips and oil.
Stir until mixed and add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Pour mixture over cereal.
Make sure cereal is well coated, then pour into paper bag.
Pour powdered sugar into bag.
Close bag and shake well.
Add more sugar if needed and shake again.
Keeps best in refrigerator or freezer.

title: chili cheese balls
directions: Place Velveeta cheese and cream cheese in a large bowl at room temperature.
Mix the cheeses well.
Add nuts and garlic powder. Mix well.
Shape in balls or logs.
Roll in chili powder.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Chill until firm.
Makes 4 or 5.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Fry bacon; add onion and brown slightly.
Set bacon and onion aside.
Drain off most of bacon fat.
In remaining fat, brown stew beef.
Sprinkle with flour, marjoram and thyme.
Stir in bouillon and wine, then add onions and bacon.
Place in large covered casserole.
Bake for 3 to 4 hours in 250° oven (covered) or microwave about 1 1/2 hours on "Simmer" level.

title: pistachio pudding cake
directions: Blend softened butter, flour and nuts until meaty.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pat firmly.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove and set aside to cool.
Whip cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Blend in 1/2 Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust and refrigerate for 20 minutes.
Mix pudding with milk with a mixer.
Spread on chilled mixture.
Set for 20 minutes.
Spread remaining Cool Whip.

title: champagne (or champagneless) punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except champagne or sparkling water. Add the champagne or sparkling water just before serving.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: allie's cornbread-biscuit dressing
directions: Crumble breads; add onion, celery and eggs.
Stir in broth; add sage and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Cook 1 pound shrimp for 3 minutes or until pink.
In separate pan heat margarine, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
When melted, stir in cooked shrimp.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients, working in sausage and cheese well.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Serve hot.
May be frozen and reheated later.

title: seafood etouffee(catfish, crawfish and shrimp)
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper and garlic until transparent.
Add Ro-Tel.
Cook until thick.
Add mushroom soup and seafood.
Cook on low fire about 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Cook frozen vegetables according to package; drain. Chop boiled eggs and onion. Combine ingredients. Add mayonnaise, mustard and Good Seasons.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except milk and cook over low heat until thick.
When cool, thin with a can of milk.

title: easy "hot" pickles
directions: Drain pickles and slice.
Drain again.
Refill gallon jar with a few pickles, a dash of Tabasco and some sugar.
Repeat until all used.
Tighten lid.
Let stand at room temperature, turning jar several times daily.
Let stand for 5 to 7 days.
Refrigerate. Pickles will be crispy crunchy.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Make syrup by boiling sugar, vinegar and spices together.
Add peaches and cook until tender and syrup is clear.
Place carefully in hot sterile jars. Seal. Store in cool area and wait a few weeks before using.
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: cracker dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, chill and serve with vegetables and crackers.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream the cream cheese with margarine and vanilla in mixer bowl at low speed.
Add confectioners sugar.
Good on carrot cake.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat together egg, water, salt, oil and coloring.
Stir in flour, a little at a time, then turn on floured surface and work until not too sticky.
Roll out and cut.
Roll real thin, then roll up like cinnamon roll and cut thin.
Allow to dry.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; stir in pan and then add boiling water.
Boil until it forms a ball, when testing by dropping a small amount at a time to make a little ball.
Add vanilla and nuts.
When it begins to sugar, turn out on waxed paper and separate each half.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and orange in a food processor.
Pour into a bowl and stir.
Mix in sugar.
Place in a covered container and refrigerate.
Allow to ripen for 2 days before serving.
Serve relish with meat or fowl.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender and drain; saute onions in margarine. Add salt, pepper, egg and thins.
Mix well and pour into a greased casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Very good.

title: macadamia nut cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Prepare Honey Bun Schemers. Spread bottom and sides of a 9 inch round cake pan.
With an electric mixer combine cream cheese and sugar, beat until smooth. Stir in flour and vanilla.
Add 1 egg and blend well; scrape bowl. Add remaining 2 eggs; blend well.
Combine nuts.
Pour batter over crust, sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 25 minutes or until firm.

title: potato rolls
directions: Combine flour, salt, yeast and sugar.
Mix in mixer.
Heat water and oleo until warm.
Add to top ingredients.
Mix.
Add potatoes.
Add more flour, if needed.
Knead until smooth.
Let rest about 10 minutes.
Knead again and shape into balls.
Place into greased baking pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, 18 to 20 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Fry sausage until done.
Saute onion until soft.
Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in a large bowl.
Layer in 13 x 9-inch pan, starting with noodles, then mix the cheese, etc.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together at once.
Chill about 1/2 hour before serving.
Dip with fresh vegetables.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Mix eggs, vanilla, sugar and salt.
Slowly add oleo, flour and cocoa.
Mix and pour in quiche.
Bake in microwave on High 5 minutes, turning after 2 minutes, then another 2 minutes, then 1 minute.
Let stand.
If not done, then cook 1 more minute. Then if not done, cut all but the middle and cook the middle an additional 1 minute.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions. Sprinkle with salt. Let stand 1 hour, then drain.

title: blueberry swirl
directions: In a blender or food processor, place cottage cheese.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Add berries, banana and Equal.
Cover and blend or process until smooth, scraping down sides occasionally. Cover and chill.
Yields 3 servings.

title: crunchy parmesan chicken
directions: Combine onions, cheese, crumbs and seasonings.
Dip chicken in egg and milk.
Coat with onion-cheese mixture.
Place in large glass (13 x 9-inch) dish and pour butter all over.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
NO cover.
(Put any extra onion-cheese mixture over top of chicken before pouring butter on.)

title: whipped potatoes
directions: Grease a 1-quart baking dish.
Make potatoes; stir well.
Beat the cream cheese with fork.
Stir into potatoes.
Add egg, onion and parsley.
Put all ingredients into a greased bowl.
Top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: low-calorie bran muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add bran and raisins, blend. Combine remaining ingredients and add to flour mixture; blend. Pour into greased loaf pan or a small cake pan (or can put in muffin tin).
Bake 35 to 50 minutes or until done.
Muffins would need to be checked a little sooner.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix yeast, 1 teaspoon flour, 1 teaspoon sugar and water; let stand.
Cream shortening, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, eggs, milk and 2 cups flour.
Add yeast mixture; beat with beater until blended and fluffy.
Add mace and lemon juice.
Knead in 3 cups flour until smooth; let rise, punch down.
Put in two 9 x 13-inch cake pans.
Top with melted butter, cinnamon and sugar.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: applesauce brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat and beat in sugar, eggs, applesauce and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Spread mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fig jelly
directions: Peel figs and mash real fine.
Take 3 cups of sugar and add to figs; boil for 5 minutes.	Add jello and boil 1 minute longer.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in salt water until tender.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Mix and cook next four ingredients.
Add mushroom soup to cooked sauce.
Pour sauce over cooked cabbage.
Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs over sauce.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Combine beef and onion in skillet.
Cook until meat is brown. Drain grease off.
Add salt, pepper, ketchup and tomato sauce and bring to boil.
Pour into casserole dish.
Lay cheese slices on, then biscuits.
Bake until biscuits are brown in a 400° oven.

title: light 'n fruity pies
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir constantly until gelatin is thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.

title: boiled chocolate cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats until well blended.
Drop on wax paper.
Cool until firm!

title: english trifle
directions: In a small bowl make raspberry jello, using most of juice from cocktail and pineapple (reserve 1/4 to 1/2 cup) plus water to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
While jello is getting very thick (but not set), in approximately 1 1/2-quart size serving bowl, line bottom of bowl with cake spread with jam.
Add sherry and enough of remaining juice to soak cake; mash with fork.
Cover with alternate layers of coconut, crumbled cookies, fruit cocktail, cookies, coconut and pineapple.
Pour very thick jello over all and leave to set.
When jello has set, prepare vanilla pudding, using 1 3/4 cups milk, and pour over the set jello mixture.
Let set.
Decorate with Cool Whip and slivered almonds and serve.
Yum!!
Yum!!

title: mexican tortilla breakfast
directions: Cut sausage links into 1/4-inch pieces and brown in skillet on medium heat.
Remove and drain.
In skillet, saute onion, green pepper and celery until tender.
Stir in chili powder, oregano, salt, sugar and juice from tomatoes.
Add tomatoes and sausage. Mix well.
Simmer, uncovered, to thicken.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix thoroughly sugar, shortening, egg. Stir in milk. Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder, salt. Blend in berries. Spread in greased and floured 9-inch square pan.

title: bavarian pork and sauerkraut
directions: Brown pork in skillet with oil, garlic and onion.
Do not overcook the garlic or onion.
In a separate saucepan, put sauerkraut, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil and cook down to 1/2 the amount.
Add caraway seed.
Combine sauerkraut with pork and simmer 40 minutes.
Do not allow to go dry.
Add wine and simmer 5 minutes; serve.

title: parmesan potato nuggets
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, onion salt and paprika in plastic bag.
Microwave (High) margarine in small dish for 1 minute or until melted.
Drain potatoes.
Coat potatoes with flour, shaking off excess.
Dip into margarine, then in plastic bag with crumbs to coat evenly.
Arrange on lightly greased glass plate.
Cover with paper towel.
Microwave (High) for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender, rotating plate twice.
Serve warm on toothpicks.
Makes 40 nuggets, 25 calories each.

title: sweet cinnamon quick bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine all bread ingredients; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pan immediately.
Refrigerate leftover bread.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: french-style string beans
directions: Mix and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Drain and serve cold.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in bowl. Add sugar and cinnamon. Mix well.
Place apple mixture in buttered 9-inch pie dish.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Put 2 tablespoons margarine in skillet.
Saute 2 cloves crushed garlic and 1 large chopped onion. Cut zucchini into sticks (remove skin, suggested).
Add parsley and Italian seasoning. Saute all together until tender, not soft.
Pour 1/2 cup tomato sauce (or more to taste) over top.
Sprinkle with 1 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese. Cover with lid until cheese melts.
Serves about 6 to 8 as a side dish (less if some are hungry).

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve hot or cold.

title: quick and easy mexican dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on a plate. Pour the jar of salsa over the cream cheese, then top with the shredded Cheddar. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on cookie sheet and bake as instructed on package.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread mixture on baked crust.
Put raw vegetables and cheese on crust.
Heat up or serve raw, cooled.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in pan. Blend mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Pour on top of salad.

title: chicken c-bleu
directions: Place each chicken piece between sheets of waxed paper. Flatten with meat mallet.
Place flattened breasts on board with flat side down.
Put cheese and ham slices to corner of chicken, then roll up.
Secure with toothpick.
Roll in flour.
Salt and pepper.
Brown in 1/4 cup butter on all sides.
Reduce heat to low and add wine and simmer 20 minutes, then place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Melt 6 tablespoons butter in saucepan and add onion. Cook until tender.
Blend salt, pepper and 1/4 cup flour.
Add milk and light cream and stir until smooth.
Add wine from skillet and cook over moderately low heat until sauce is thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake uncovered in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice adding sauce on top.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Blend together Crisco, 1 pound sugar, salt and 1/4 cup water, then add remaining sugar and water.
Add butter and vanilla flavorings.
Beat on high speed for 10 minutes.

title: creamy low-cholesterol eggnog
directions: In container of electric blender, combine egg substitute, water, dry milk, sugar, vanilla and a dash of nutmeg.
Add 6 ice cubes.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth.
With motor running, remove feeder cap and gradually add remaining 6 ice cubes.
Continue blending until smooth.
Pour into cups; garnish each serving with a sprinkle of nutmeg.

title: tomato artichoke bake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a 1-quart baking dish. Saute onion and green onion in margarine until tender.
Add tomatoes, artichoke hearts and basil.
Stir gently over medium heat 2 or 3 minutes.
Season with salt, pepper and sugar.
Turn into baking dish and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 minutes until vegetables are heated through and cheese is lightly brown and bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar and flour and then add milk.
Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Add coconut and pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites with 2 tablespoons sugar; top pie and brown.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan. Mix together flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Add brown sugar, walnuts, butter, eggs and vanilla, stirring just to combine.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 25 minutes or until golden brown and firm.
Remove from oven.
Place pan on wire rack and cool 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks well.
In medium bowl, mix coconut and sour cream.
Carefully fold in drained oranges and pineapple chunks.
Serve in individual dessert dishes. Garnish with almonds and cherries.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces. Dice onion and brown together and drain. Add all ingredients EXCEPT rice. Simmer on medium-low for 30 minutes. Turn down to low. Add rice. Stir and shut off burner. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes for rice to soak up juices.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and cook to soft ball. Cool in cold water until you can stand your hand to touch bottom of pan.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and Karo and bring to a boil.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and margarine. Beat until creamy and pour into buttered dish and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: date nut bars
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Stir in Bisquick mix, pecans and dates.
Mixture will be thick.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 1 hour.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Empty kidney beans into colander.
Rinse with hot water to remove sauce.
Drain and chill.
Mix mayonnaise with catsup. Combine with beans and other ingredients.
Serve on lettuce, if desired.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Fry hamburger and onions until done, then add all of the other ingredients.
Cook about 1 hour or until excess juice is gone.

title: chile rellenos
directions: Take 1/2 of can of green chile and line bottom of oblong casserole dish.
Layer with strips of Jack cheese, remaining chile and Cheddar cheese.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks and evaporated milk.
Then add together and beat.
Add flour and salt; beat and pour over layers.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Top with tomato sauce and cook another 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf with vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hearty ribs and beans
directions: Place ribs in an ungreased 13x9x2 inch baking pan, add water. Cover and bake at 350° for 1-1/2 hour, drain, reserving liquid. Skim fat, set ribs aside.
Add enough water to liquid to measure 1 c. place in a saucepan.
Add tomato sauce, soup mix, sugar, mustard
and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes, reserve 1/2 c. to the remaining sauce.
Add beans, celery and red pepper. Pour into baking pan, add ribs, pour reserved sauce over ribs. Cover and bake for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Yield 6-8 servings.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix the pudding and Cool Whip together thoroughly.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Line dish with a layer of the crackers. Place a layer of pudding/Cool Whip on top of the crackers.
Repeat these steps 2 more times, then line the top with graham crackers.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in apples and nuts.

title: bite-sized burgers
directions: Mix ground beef in a large bowl with all of the ingredients except flour.
Blend well.
Form into balls about 1/2-inch in diameter.
Roll in flour; fry quickly in hot oil.
Serve warm.

title: hot crab dip for crock-pot
directions: Cook all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook (about 30 minutes until the cheese melts using high setting).
Turn to low and cook 3 to 4 hours.
Add more milk if too thick.
Serve warm or cold on crackers.

title: potato cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Mayonnaise may be added if needed or more sour cream may be added for consistency.

title: cauliflower-ham casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in boiling water about 10 minutes. Drain and set aside. In saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter; stir in flour. Add milk. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Add cheese; stir until melted. Stir in cooked vegetable, ham and mushrooms. Pour into 2-quart casserole. Combine bread crumbs and melted 1 tablespoon butter. Sprinkle over vegetable mixture. Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced tealubbock, texas
directions: Put 3 tsp. mixture in 1 cup hot water for individual servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix yeast in lukewarm water; set aside.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add oil, salt and 2 cups of bread flour and mix well. Add boiling water to this mixture, mixing well.
Then add the cup of dissolved yeast and mix well.
Add remaining flour, mixing well.
(It is best to use your electric mixer before you add the last two cups of flour.) Place in a spot where there is no draft. Let rise double in size.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken in water until tender.
Remove skin and debone. Save broth.
In a large casserole dish put chicken, soup, vegetables and pimentos.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Top with pie crust and cut a slit in the top for the steam.
This can be made up a day ahead of time and refrigerated.
Bake at 400° until the crust is done.

title: wild bird seed cookies for birds
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender or knives until crumbly. Add eggs and mix to make firm dough.
Add bird seed and knead until smooth.
Wrap in waxed paper and plastic bag and chill thoroughly.

title: jam cake
directions: Bake in tube pan at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Put big pan under cake.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook the shrimp as directed on the Chesapeake Bay seasoning label until the shrimp are pink.
Rinse and devein.
Cook shells 12 minutes; drain and rinse.
In a large bowl, cut up crab in bite size pieces; cut shrimp in half and add chopped eggs, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Squeeze a few drops of lime juice to taste. Store in refrigerator two hours before serving.
You may have to add more lime juice and mayonnaise.
Serves eight.

title: herb cheese-beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a large loaf pan.
In a medium bowl, mix together all the dry ingredients.
Stir in beer and cheese and blend together well.
Spread mixture evenly into prepared pan.
Bake approximately 50 to 55 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack to cool.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems.
Melt 2 sticks butter.
Add stems and bread crumbs to butter.
Add bread crumbs until good consistency for stuffing.
Stuff mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: doris' lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onions; add rest of ingredients and simmer for at least 4 hours.
Cook noodles according to package directions, adding 2 tablespoons olive oil to the water.
To assemble, put a little sauce in the bottom of the baking dish; lay noodles on top and top with more sauce, Mozzarella and a sprinkling of Parmesan. Continue layering, ending with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until cheese is lightly browned and bubbly.

title: shrimp oreganata
directions: Toss shrimp and all ingredients in bowl until well covered. Place layered in pan on low heat until pink on both sides and cooked.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown each side of roast in frying pan.
Mix and heat in crock-pot the last 4 ingredients.
Add roast and cook on low heat 10 to 12 hours.
Chop.
Drain 2 cups of broth and add ketchup. Put chopped meat into crock-pot.
Add broth and ketchup; cook about 2 more hours.

title: oatmeal - chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix together with flour and oatmeal. Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and chopped nuts. Roll into balls and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pork chops and orange rice
directions: Brown the pork chops in skillet. Season with salt and pepper. Place rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour in orange juice. Place pork chops on top. Spoon soup over all.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes, then bake, uncovered, for 10 more minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Beat Crisco and cottage cheese together.
Knead in the flour. Makes 6 to 8 crusts.

title: oven stew
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients in a pan.
Bring to boil on top of stove, then cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Add vegetables and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.

title: refrigerator fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack firmly into vanilla wafer box.
Secure box with tape or string; place in refrigerator for 7 days.
Carefully cut box away from cake; slice and serve.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: Heat 2 cups of the milk in a saucepan.
Put the sugar, cocoa, flour and salt and the other 1/2 cup of milk in a bowl.
Add to the hot milk; cook until it comes to a boil and thickens.
Cook 10 minutes more; then add the 2 egg yolks, slightly beaten and cook for 2 minutes longer.
Take off stove and add the butter or margarine and the vanilla.
Place in a pie shell with Cool Whip or make a meringue, using the two egg whites, 2 or 4 tablespoons sugar, 1/8 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put ground chuck in square baking dish.
Pat it down; salt and pepper it.
Smooth the soup on top of hamburger.
Sprinkle the grated cheese on top of soup.
Place the Tater Tots close together on top of that.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain.
Add all other ingredients. Turn on low heat and simmer while you make biscuits or you can use canned biscuits.
Homemade biscuits are better.
Place biscuits on top meat after placing in casserole bowl or pan.
Bake at 450° until biscuits are done.

title: low-fat chicken fried rice
directions: Cube the chicken breasts.
Coat a wok or frying pan with nonstick spray.
Stir-fry the chicken until done, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Take chicken out; set aside.
Combine all vegetables together with 1/2 cup water; cook until tender, about 8 minutes. Cook rice separately until done.
Add garlic powder, parsley, lite salt and lemon pepper to vegetables.
Add chicken back to vegetables; add in the cooked rice.
Add 1/4 cup soy sauce or to taste.
Mix and serve.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix chicken, celery, rice and onion; add salt and place mixture in 2-quart casserole.

title: hamburger barley soup
directions: Combine all but last 2 ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add carrots and simmer 10 minutes more.
Add potato and simmer 20 minutes more.

title: christmas tree cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Mix in eggs, heavy cream and vanilla.
Blend in flour and baking powder.
Cover.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.

title: crazy cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add the oil, vinegar, cold water and vanilla.
Do not grease pan!
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: california white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream and oleo in heavy pan; bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in white chocolate until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until well blended. Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: ploy pancakes
directions: If too yellow, add 1 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Add water until creamy (2 cups).
Fry on ungreased pan.
Serve with beans, hot dogs, etc.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325° .
Lightly grease a baking sheet.
Knead by hand to mix ingredients.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Let drain and serve hot. This dough can be frozen for later baking.
Makes up to 56 balls.

title: pepper biscuits
directions: Cut together flour, baking powder and shortening.
Mix pepper, salt and butter; then add to first mixture.
Flour hands.
Roll in hands to form biscuits.
Pat tops slightly to flatten.
Put on greased tray.
Bake on 2nd rack at 450° or 500° for 8 to 10 minutes, until tops are browned.

title: ernie's tortellini soup
directions: Mix together in large pan 8 c. water, bouillon cube and chicken broth.
Add tomatoes with their juice.
Bring to a boil. Cook box of tortellini for about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, micro-cook spinach until done.
Add spinach and ranch dressing mix to pot.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Makes 12 cups.

title: tuna caesar salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir first 7 ingredients until smooth.
Add lettuce and toss to coat.
Add tuna and croutons.
Makes 4 servings.

title: christmas congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order listed and mix well. Cool overnight in refrigerator.

title: asparagus canapes
directions: Cut crust off bread and roll out flat.
Spread with mixture of cheese, mayonnaise and egg.
Top each slice of bread with 1 stalk of asparagus.
Roll up and cut into 3 pieces.
Dip into melted butter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
May be made before and frozen before.

title: egg nog pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, egg nog, milk and nutmeg in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat to full boil.
Remove from heat; add rum and cool 5 minutes; stirring twice.
Pour into pie shell; cover with plastic wrap.
Chill 3 hours.
Garnish with Cool Whip and nutmeg.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Mash bananas very fine.
Add sugar and beaten egg.
Mix flour and soda; add to first.
Add melted butter and vanilla.
If wanted, add 1 to 2 cups chopped walnuts.
Put into prepared loaf pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Dump into mixing bowl and mix with electric beater (using bread hook). Blend with hands.
Pinch off required amount and refrigerate remainder.
Also freezes well. Makes enough for 3 single shells.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring the water, margarine and cocoa to a boil.
Set aside to cool.
Mix the flour, sugar and salt.
Add the first 3 ingredients to the dry ingredients.
Beat well the eggs, sour cream and baking soda; mix all together.
Pour into an 11 x 17-inch pan or cookie sheet (greased).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon butter
directions: Place all ingredients in a food processor and blend until mixture is smooth. Serve with hot rolls or muffins; great on sweet potatoes!

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix shrimp with electric beater.
Add cream cheese and blend. Add onion to taste, 1 to 2 teaspoons catsup and milk so consistency is smooth.
(Use more catsup than milk.)
Best when made the day before.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan over low heat, combine chili sauce and jelly. Stir occasionally until jelly melts.
(In microwave on High, 1 to 2 minutes.)
Set aside. In a large bowl, combine meat and rest of the ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls.
Place in deep baking dish. Pour sauce over meatballs, making sure all balls are covered. Bake 35 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine and add to pretzels.
If using pecans, do not use 1/2 cup of the pretzels.
Press mixture in oblong dish.
Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Pour on top of pretzels.
Put pineapple juice in boiler and add 2 teaspoons cornstarch and 1/2 cup sugar and let cook until thick.
Cool completely.
Add pineapple and spread on top of second layer. Keep in refrigerator.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a baking dish.
Combine fruit, 1 cup sugar and water.
Pour into baking dish.
Mix together remaining sugar, flour, milk, vanilla and Crisco.
Pour over fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, cream cheese and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Add flour.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili cheese steak
directions: Mix flour, salt, chili powder and pepper. Coat meat with mixture and brown on both sides. Saut onion. Put onion and meat in a baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover and top with cheese. Return to oven until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: cinnamon ice shake
directions: In a blender mix all the ingredients.
After blending, let the shake set for about 30 seconds or more.
Then if you want, spray Cool Whip on top.
Serves about 2 people.

title: pork chops and cabbage dinner
directions: In skillet, cook chops in oil until brown on both sides. Remove chops from skillet and add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in wine vinegar, salt, pepper, white wine and brown sugar.
Stir in cabbage and apples.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Top with chops. Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes or till chops are done.

title: hot sandwiches
directions: Grind together the cheese, green pepper, onion and bacon.
Add the dry mustard.
Slice buns. Spread with butter and mixture. Cook under broiler until brown.

title: stained glass cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and oleo in double boiler.
Do not cook. Add M&M's and nuts. Sprinkle sheet of foil with coconut.
Pour chocolate mixture over the coconut and roll up.
Chill and slice when firm.

title: pasta with peas
directions: Put oil, onion, margarine and bacon into large pasta pan over low heat.
When onions are soft, add juice of peas and water to the handle marks.
Add the tomato sauce, salt and pepper to taste, beef bouillon and baking soda.
Cook for 20 minutes at slow boil.
Add macaroni and cook for 5 minutes.
Add peas and grated cheese and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: herbed tomato tart
directions: Place crust in 10 inch pie plate.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°. Remove from oven and cool slightly.
Remove seeds from tomatoes slices.
Layer tomatoes slices in paper towels and pat dry.
Set aside.
In food processor, combine chopped basil, marjoram, parsley, garlic, 2 Tbsp. oil and 1/2 tsp. salt.
Spread herb paste in bottom of warm crust.
Layer tomato slices in concentric circles over herb mixture.
Scatter olive slices and goat cheese over tomatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drizzle with 1 to 2 Tbsp. olive oil.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, until crust is golden and cheese is softened and nicely browned. Yield 5 servings.

title: chicken ole
directions: Put breasts in greased casserole dish.
Spoon salsa over top. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: chicken divan
directions: Sear beef in a little cooking oil in heavy pot.
Add enough water to just cover beef and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add remainder of ingredients and bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer for 1 hour, stirring so it does not burn. Simmer 30 minutes, during which time, check seasonings.
Beans may be added, if desired.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend on lowest speed until smooth.

title: chocolate chiffon cake
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer let egg whites warm to room temperature about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Place cocoa in small bowl.
Add boiling water.
Stir until smooth.
Let mixture cool about 20 minutes.

title: fat-free cream soup mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
To make soup base, add 2 cups cold water to the mix in a large saucepan and stir constantly over medium heat until thick.

title: southwest chicken
directions: Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken, chili powder and garlic salt.
Cook until chicken is no longer pink.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add water to reserved liquid to make 1 cup.
Add liquid and picante sauce to skillet; bring to a boil. Stir in rice and reduce heat.
Cover tightly and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in beans and tomatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with sprinkled Cheddar cheese.

title: easy breakfast  cheese quiche
directions: Start with 1 cup milk, add all other ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Add remainder of milk if needed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can be frozen and cooked later.
Cook at 350° for 50 to 60
minutes.

title: shrimp dip(ruby mcinvale)
directions: Mix all ingredients
together;
use
milk if mixture is stiff. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: deviled crab casserole
directions: Mix bread crumbs with melted margarine.
Reserve 1/4 cup.

title: rich nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixer combine all the ingredients except confectioners' sugar and mix until smooth.
Roll dough into balls about 1 inch in diameter, place on a greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart, and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
They should just be turning golden brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while still hot. Yield:
5 dozen.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Mix everything in a pot and simmer for at least 1 hour.
It is best cooked a day or so ahead and reheated.
It freezes well.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Combine cereal and pecans in a 13 by 9 inch pan. Set aside.

title: fruit smash punch
directions: Make jello in usual manner; add cold water and fruit juices. Stir in sugar.
Just before serving, mash or whip bananas until smooth and creamy.
Beat into mixture.
Add ginger ale, the last minute.

title: irish coffee
directions: Beat whipping cream, powdered sugar and vanilla in chilled small mixing bowl until stiff.
Refrigerate.
Prepare coffee using 3/4 cup coffee and 3 cups water.
Heat 4 mugs.
Place 1 or 2 teaspoons of sugar and 2 tablespoons of whiskey in each mug. Stir; pour hot coffee into each mug.
Top with whipped cream. Serve immediately.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all the above ingredients and serve chilled.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix all together in bowl to be passed or in oblong dish to be cut in squares.

title: t-l-t's
directions: Cook turkey bacon as directed on package in microwave oven. Spread toasted bread with mayonnaise; top with lettuce, tomato and 3 slices bacon.
Put second slice of toasted bread on top.
Makes 2 sandwiches.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all this together.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes at 300°.

title: pig lickin' cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oranges, eggs and oil all together.
Pour into greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk together and pour into melted butter.
Do not stir.
Spoon pie filling into middle of dough mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: cream cheese-butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and butter bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover bottom of pan with one can of rolls.
Spread cream cheese over rolls.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon and vanilla; sprinkle half over cream cheese.
Put second can of rolls over this. Spread melted stick of butter over this second layer of rolls. Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture over this.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Refrigerate if not using immediately (after cooling).

title: asparagus soup salad
directions: Heat soup and water.
Add jello; add cream cheese while water is still warm.
Cool and add other ingredients; grease mold and pour mixture in mold.
Chill and unmold.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and peanut butter, beating well.
Add vanilla, oats and soda.
Mix well.
Put teaspoon of mixture on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with floured fork.
Bake in a 350° oven about 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 7 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: shrimp party mold
directions: Soften gelatin in milk.
Heat soup and cream cheese over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in softened gelatin.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased 4 cup mold. Chill several hours until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: sliced cucumbers and onions
directions: Bring the last five ingredients to a boil; cool.
Pour over sliced cucumbers and onions.
Keeps for several days.

title: fruit salad surprise
directions: Mix and chill 24 hours and serve.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Roll each biscuit flat and wrap around Vienna sausage.
Bake 10 minutes at 375° or until brown.
(Precooked wieners may be used.)

title: german chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients and mix at low speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in morsels and spoon in Bundt pan. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 10 minutes and remove from pan. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mozzarella pinwheel(meat loaf)
directions: In a large bowl, combine ground beef, onion, bread crumbs, eggs, tomato sauce and spices.
Mix well and transfer to a rectangle piece of Saran plastic wrap.
Pat out meat mixture to a flat rectangle.
Sprinkle with the dry bread crumbs, then sprinkle on the shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up like a jelly roll. Place in a shallow baking pan and bake in a slow oven at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool 5 minutes before slicing.
Cool 5 minutes before slicing.
Serve with Ragu sauce sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables, mayonnaise, cheese and onion.
Top with crushed crackers that have been combined with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sorrel soup(zaudum)
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, carrot, celery and ham.
Cover with water in Dutch oven.
Add seasonings and bouillon.
Boil until potatoes are tender.
Add sorrell.
Make a paste of 3/4 cup of sour cream and 2 tablespoons of flour; add to cooked potatoes. Stir until thickened.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Simmer onions in oil.
When onions brown, add chicken and water.
After 1 hour, add pepper, celery, potatoes and tomato sauce mix.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Add noodles about 10 minutes before serving.

title: jiffy cake delight
directions: Mix cake as per box instructions and bake for 15 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend pudding, milk and cream cheese until smooth (make pudding and blend in the cream cheese).
Spread over cooled cake.
Spread crushed pineapple and then cover with lots of Cool Whip (about 1 to 2 inches thick).
Top with nuts and cherries if you like.
Chill and serve.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make Roux:
Get oil hot in heavy pan.
Gradually add flour, stirring continuously, until well mixed.
Lower heat and continue stirring until peanut butter color.
Set aside.

title: tuna-macaroni casserole
directions: Place tuna
in
casserole
dish with onion, celery, egg and soup; mix
well.
Cook macaroni in salted water and drain. Put macaroni
over
tuna
in casserole dish and place Velveeta cheese strips
over
top
of casserole.
Tomato slices can be added over cheese strips.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add sifted dry ingredients and carrots. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add nuts and cherries and mix well.
Bake in oiled loaf pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cover cake with aluminum foil for first 20 minutes. Remove foil and continue baking.

title: apple nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, mix thoroughly and pour into two greased 9 3/4 x 5 3/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoon or roll balls.
If rolled balls, crisscross with floured fork.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: two minute microwave fudge
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir sugar, cocoa, milk, salt and vanilla together until partially blended.
Put butter over top in center of dish.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes or until milk feels warm on bottom of dish.
Stir vigorously until smooth. Blend in nuts.
Pour onto wax paper-lined 8 x 4 x 3-inch dish. Chill 1 hour in refrigerator or 20 to 30 minutes in freezer.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 36 squares.

title: easy fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large saucepan, over low heat, melt 1 cup chips with butter. Remove from heat.
Add Bisquick mix, milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining 1 cup chips.
Turn into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from the sides of the pan. Cool. Frost, if desired.
Cut into bars.
Makes 24 to 36 bars. Store at room temperature.

title: halupki
directions: Core cabbage and put in warm water.
Let it boil; cover and leave for about 10 minutes.
Break leaves off.
Mix ground beef, salt, pepper, eggs, onion, 1/4 tomato sauce and rice together in a bowl.
Take cabbage leaf and put 1 to 2 tablespoons of ground beef mixture in it.
Roll cabbage.
Place cabbage rolls in a roaster pan with edge of folded side down.
Place sauerkraut over top.
Pour 1/2 can of tomato sauce on top.
Bake at 325° for at least 2 hours.

title: zesty cheddar cheese balls
directions: In medium bowl, work all ingredients together with a fork until mixture is well blended.
Knead mixture with hands until smooth.
Roll into one-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done; debone and cut into cubes.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Add chicken to sour cream mixture. Pour into casserole dish.
Crumble the Ritz crackers on top.
Cut butter and place on top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Lightly grease a 9 X 13-inch pan.
Place 1 tube of crescent rolls on bottom of pan.
Butter fingers and press out into corners.

title: zesty sauce(for beef, chicken or shrimp)
directions: Combine all ingredients; heat.
Use as meatloaf sauce.
Makes 2 cups.

title: julius' meat chili for hot dogs
directions: Put onions and ground beef in a large pan; mix well and add water to cover. Salt and pepper generously. Bring to a boil and boil gently for 20 to 30 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, dish onto boiled hot dogs in steamed buns.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Thoroughly brown the meat on all sides in hot fat, turning often.
Add water, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, sliced onion and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
Add carrots, onions and potatoes.
(Cut up carrots and potatoes.)
Cover and cook 30 minutes more, or until vegetables are done.
Thicken liquid for gravy.

title: rice pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and margarine.
Stir until margarine is melted.
Slowly add milk mixture to eggs, stirring constantly.
Mix in rice, raisins and vanilla.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until knife inserted is clean, in a 350° oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain all vegetables in a colander.

title: koulourakia (cookies)(greek)
directions: Allow butter to soften at room temperature.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla, beating all the while.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into mixture and combine.
Knead until well blended.
Shape each cookie.
Place on oiled baking sheet, 2 inches apart and glaze tops with beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: francesca and alessandra's macaroni and cheese(or fettucini alfredo)
directions: Boil fettucini in 6-quarts of water. Drain when al dente. Melt butter over low heat.
Add garlic.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes, then add all other ingredients. Remove from heat.
Toss in large bowl with noodles until well blended.
Serve with crusty Italian bread and a tossed salad.

title: grandma's cheese freeze
directions: Chill milk overnight. (It has to be real cold.) Mix 1 cup boiling water to jello. Set it in refrigerator to cool. (Do not let set.) Cream sugar and cream cheese. Add jello mix and whip. Whip up milk to a good thickness. (Will look like whip cream.) Add cream cheese mixture to milk; whip up real good. Pour into crust. (You can also add strawberries or cherries on top.) Let set in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-roni as directed on package.
Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Add with remaining ingredients to cooled Rice-A-Roni.
Refrigerate.
Better if refrigerated overnight.

title: chicken and deer mix
directions: Boil chicken and deer roast separately until the meat comes easily off the bone.
Drain and pull off in pieces.
Mix the deer and chicken.
Add butter and sauce.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: rita's pea salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine peas, celery, cheese, olives and onion.
In small bowl, blend remaining ingredients until smooth. Stir into pea mixture; mix well.
Cover and chill before serving. Serves 4.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Press into a 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix these dry ingredients and store in tightly covered jar. Put 2 teaspoons of mix in cup and add boiling water for a single serving. Serves many.

title: grandma's cake donuts
directions: Cream the butter and the sugar.
Add the eggs, slightly beaten.
Add milk, vanilla and lemon.
Stir in the flour and baking powder.
Cool for about 1 hour.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter until tender, but not browned.
Stir in flour.
Add milk; cook until mixture bubbles, stirring constantly.
Season with salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Place layer of noodles in buttered baking dish; cover with ham and sauce.
Repeat layers.
Mix bread crumbs with remaining butter.
Cook over medium heat until crisp. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: squash-onion casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients
except
cheese and bacon.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle cheese and crumbled bacon on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken before mixing with other ingredients.
Best to refrigerate overnight before served.

title: coke roast
directions: Score roast in several places.
Fill each slit with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Sear roast on all sides in oil.
Remove, drain or blot fat from roast.
Place roast in foil lined pan.
Pour Coke, and chili sauce over roast; add Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Cover loosely with foil and bake 3 hours in 325° oven.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Spray pan before cooking. Put half of cheese mixture in bottom of pan. Mix eggs and taco sauce. Pour over cheese mixture. Top with remaining cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Stir together egg, milk and oil; stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Gently fold in blueberries; fill greased muffin tins 1/2 full of batter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: brownie mound cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Mix margarine with sugar.
Stir in syrup and eggs.
Stir in flour, chocolate, vanilla and walnuts.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.
These cookies get soft and chewy when stored overnight in an airtight Tupperware type container.
They also freeze well.

title: corn au gratin
directions: Mix all together.
Place in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix about 3/4 of the cheese with chili in a large bowl.
Fill each flour tortilla with approximately 2 tablespoons of mixture. Roll up and place in greased pan.
After filling tortillas, put any remaining chili on top of enchiladas and spread top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 450° until cheese melts.

title: goetta
directions: Brown meat.
Cook oats for 10 minutes.
Mix with other ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour in loaf pans.
Let set for 1 hour and then brown.

title: lamb t-bone
directions: Preheat broiler.
Dry lamb with paper toweling; trim excess fat.
Season with pepper and salt.
Brush rack with oil.
Arrange lamb in a single layer on rack.
Broil 2 inches from heat.
Cook 3 minutes per side or to desired doneness.

title: marshmallow nut puffs
directions: Dip marshmallows in hot cream which has been flavored with vanilla until outside of marshmallow is soft.
Roll in finely ground pecans.
Flatten slightly.
Chill.

title: simple and delicious onion rings
directions: Slice onions into 1/4-inch rings; dip in buttermilk.
Put fish fry into 2 Ziploc bags, drop in onions and seal.
Shake to coat, then drop in deep fryer and cook until brown.
(I use peanut oil.)

title: stromboli
directions: Let frozen dough thaw until pliable.
Divide in half.
On a lightly floured board, roll each dough piece out to a 9-inch square.
Cover dough with layers of pepperoni or salami, cheese and ham.
Roll each piece up like a jelly roll tightly.
Using a little flour on fingers, pinch ends and long edge of dough.
Roll tightly to seal filling inside.

title: cavatini
directions: Saute onion, pepper, pepperoni and mushrooms in oil (half done).
Add spaghetti sauce.
Cook quite awhile.
Cook pasta; drain.
Mix together in a large casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: baked ziti
directions: Mix eggs, cottage cheese and all seasoning.
Boil ziti for 15 minutes.
When drained, put 1 layer of ziti on bottom of dish, then layer of cheese mixture, then layer of Muenster cheese, then pour sauce over all.
Repeat layers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot apple toddy
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan.
Simmer 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Stir the corn syrup into bourbon.
Fork into dry mix.
Form into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container one week or longer.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and honey.
Beat eggs; add milk to eggs. Sift flour with baking powder.
Add alternately with eggs and milk to first mixture.
Add chopped figs and raisins, then add spices. (I use 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon cloves and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.)
Bake at 350° in Bundt pan or oblong pan.
Use your favorite icing.
The Word tastes great!

title: mini apple pizzas
directions: Roll or pat biscuits into 3 1/2-inch circles; place on a lightly greased baking sheet.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl mixing well.
Let rise 1 hour.
Add next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Let rise, covered, in warm place, until doubled.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Roll out on floured surface.
Spread with butter. Sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon, sugar and nuts.
Roll as for jelly roll and cut into slices.
Place in greased baking pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Frost while warm.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In casserole dish, place green beans.
Mix soup and milk; pour over beans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until it starts to brown.
Remove.
Top with onion rings.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Place washed chicken in a Dutch oven (do not pat dry).
Add onion and carrots.
Cut up margarine over top of vegetables. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer over low heat until chicken is nice and soft, about 45 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Add cream; cover and let stand 10 minutes more. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli until separated.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Mix broccoli, rice, celery and soup.
Top with cheese. Place in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix altogether and mold into desired shape.
Place in refrigerator; chill.
When ready to serve, fill center of ring with strawberry preserves.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
In a double boiler, slowly stir in flour, sugar and fruit juice.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Chill and fold in Cool Whip.

title: squash continental
directions: Cut unpared squash into 1/2 inch rounds.
Saute in mixture of butter, water, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered 6-8 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onions.
Drain.
Mix with soup and rice. Make a sauce by blending flour, broth, half and half and spices. Add to sausage mixture.
Place in a greased casserole dish and top with slivered almonds. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake mix in jelly roll pan.
Soften cream cheese and beat. Mix pudding with milk.
Add to cream cheese and beat until smooth. Add Cool Whip; mix and spread over cooled cake.
Sprinkle pineapple over cake, then sprinkle coconut and chopped nuts.
Decorate with cherries.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients together and shape into a ball. Roll in 1/2 cup chopped, salted nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour corn and juice on.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Spread on cream of chicken soup.
Pour on chicken rice soup.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: fresh fruit medley
directions: Divide fruit among 6 dessert dishes.
Just before serving, spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons fruit concentrate onto each serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage stuffing balls
directions: Combine stuffing mix with hot water. Break sausage into small pieces and add to moistened stuffing mix. Stir in onion, celery, egg and baking powder until evenly distributed. Shape into balls, using 1/4 cup mixture for each ball and place in baking pan. Cover with foil, securing tightly around pan. Bake in a slow oven (325°) 15 minutes. Remove foil. Raise oven temperature to 350° and continue baking
25 minutes or until sausage is done. Makes 18 to 22 balls.

title: mushroom-olive steak
directions: Cut steak into 6 servings.
Combine flour, salt and pepper. Dredge meat in mixture.
Brown meat in hot cooking fat.
Pour off drippings.
Add water, garlic salt, soy sauce and onion.
Cover tightly and simmer 45 minutes.
Add mushrooms last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Thicken with flour-water mixture for gravy if desired.
Fold in olives just before serving.
Serves six.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Put the ingredients in a glass bowl and bake for 1 hour at 275° or until all cubed cheese is melted.
Serve with Fritos.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: amish bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into medium size loaf pan (greased).
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crab imperial
directions: Make sauce from first 11 ingredients and cook over low heat until thickened.
Stir a little of hot mixture into 1 beaten egg, then add egg to sauce.
Add crab meat mix and put into oven-proof dish.
Combine 1/2 cup fine dry bread crumbs and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle over top and heat at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until browned on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
(Serves 4.)

title: winter soup
directions: Saute ground beef until brown.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Add all other ingredients except cabbage; simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add cabbage and cook 30 minutes longer.
Soup will thicken when lid is removed.
This soup freezes well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop ham, onions and green pepper (in food processor). Mix all ingredients well. Chill for 1 hour. Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: play dough
directions: Combine flour, salt and alum.
Mix well with water, then add oil and knead until smooth.
Add a few drops of desired food coloring.
Store in airtight container.

title: green chile enchiladas
directions: Add garlic to meat and brown.
Add Longhorn cheese and onions. Mix well.
Heat soup, milk and pasteurized cheese until cheese is melted.
Add onion dip mix, green chiles and chopped pimentos. Soften tortillas either in hot oil and drain or in microwave. Fill each tortilla with meat mixture.
Roll tightly and place in shallow baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Heat butter in double boiler; remove from heat and add flour. Return to heat; add milk gradually, stirring constantly, until sauce boils.
Add seasonings; simmer 5 minutes.
Add grated cheese and stir until melted.
Serve on toast or crackers (also good on macaroni).

title: finnish coffee bread
directions: Heat milk until warm; add melted butter.
Put 2 (1/4-ounce) packages of yeast in 1/2 cup of warm water.
Add to milk the sugar, yeast, eggs and cardamon.
Add flour; knead until firm and smooth. Cover with towel; let rise until double bulk.
Knead until smooth. Divide into 4 greased bread pans.
Cover; let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Brush with 1/2 cup coffee and 1/2 cup sugar (optional).

title: aunt ruthie's pumpkin pie
directions: Bake at 400° to 425° for 10 minutes, then 300° to 325° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Combine Rhubarb, Strawberries, Tapioca, Sugar, Salt and Nutmeg in large sauce pan.
Let stand 15 - 20 minutes.
Bring mixture to boil; stir gently until thickened.
Remove from heat and let cool for 1 hour.
Pour in pie crust and cover with pie crust.
Put lines in top of pie.
Sprinkle top with 1 - 2 teaspoons of Sugar.
Cover edges with aluminum foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 375.
Take out. Remove foil and put back in for 10 - 15 minutes.
Cool and enjoy.

title: coconut pie
directions: Read instructions very closely:

title: raisin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place raisins and water in saucepan and cook until tender.
Blend sugar with flour and add to raisin mixture and cook over low heat until thickened, stirring frequently.
Add nuts, lemon rind and juice.
Stir.
Cool and pour into pastry shell.
Seal with top crust.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: new year's day bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Place in large kettle.
Cover with water 2-inches. Add 2 tablespoons salt.
Soak overnight.
Drain in morning.
Add 2 quarts water and ham hocks or ham.
Bring to boil.
Simmer slowly 3 hours.
Add onion (tomatoes, if desired).
Season with chili powder, lemon, salt and pepper.
Remove ham hock or ham.
Cut up meat and add to soup.
Good with tossed salad and crackers.

title: wild rice baron
directions: Gently cook wild rice in water and 2 teaspoons salt for 20 minutes.
Drain, if necessary.
Brown meat.
Rinse mushrooms, cut off tops of stems, slice caps and saute with onion and celery in butter for 5 minutes.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Add slowly sugar and baking powder.
Crush 21 crackers (about 1 cup).
Add pecans to the crackers.
Fold this into egg white mixture and add vanilla. Grease a deep pie plate.
Fill and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Refrigerate overnight.
Top with whipped cream.
Use Ritz crackers.

title: christmas rocks
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients, mixing well. Add fruit and nuts; mix well. Spoon onto cookie sheet covered with parchment paper. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: nathan's favorite taco dip
directions: Spread beans on platter.
Peel and mash avocado.
Season with lemon, salt and pepper.
Mix well and spread over top of beans. Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix and spread over avocado. Sprinkle on onion tops, tomatoes and olives.
Top with grated cheese.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: grape punch
directions: Combine water, cinnamon and cloves in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Chill.
Strain. Combine chilled mixture with grape and lemon juice just before serving.
Mix well.
