Pour over ice in punch bowl. Add ginger ale. Garnish with grapes.
Makes 30 servings.

title: chicken-cucumber soup
directions: In a bowl, blend soup and sour cream until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill 3 hours.
Serve in chilled bowls. Serves 3 or 4.
A good summer soup.

title: orange ball cookies
directions: Use blender to make vanilla wafer crumbs.
Mix well with orange juice and coconut.
Use hands to form walnut sized balls. Roll in either powdered sugar or coconut.
Do not bake.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.
Put cookies in closed container.
May freeze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Saute onion in butter in large saucepan.
Add soup, mushrooms, cheese and almonds.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Mix with drained broccoli.

title: carrot ring
directions: Mix together and put in greased mold. Place in pan of water and bake for approximately 40 minutes or until set. Turn out onto serving dish and fill cavity with peas.

title: clam casserole
directions: Mix all; bake about 1 hour in a moderate oven.
Use clam juice instead of water unless you are worried about salt intake.
Serves 6 to 8.
Delicious and easy.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Peel, quarter and boil potatoes about 20 minutes and reserve 3/4 cup of the potato water.
Brown meat, pour off fat.
Add onion, celery and garlic; cook for about 10 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in potato water; add oregano, Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce, beef bouillon, salt and pepper to taste.
Combine liquid mixture with meat mixture and simmer until mixture thickens.
Prepare mashed potatoes in usual manner, put in a low casserole dish to look like a pie.
Spoon thickened meat mixture over bottom on potatoes and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese over meat mixture; return to oven until cheese is melted.
The potato crust will have browned lightly, giving the appearance of pie crust.

title: instant vegetable soup
directions: Combine water and bouillon in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; let bouillon dissolve.
Add carrots, celery, potato and rosamarina. Simmer about 10 minutes.
Saute onions in butter until soft.
Add to soup.
Make roux with remaining butter and flour.
Add more butter if preferred.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; pour in beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add the rhubarb and mix well.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 minutes or whatever time it takes for crust to brown and custard to set.
Some of rhubarb will come to the top.

title: cheesy french bread(microwave needed)
directions: Cut loaf diagonally into 1-inch slices.
Mix remaining ingredients. Spread mixture on one side of each slice of bread. Reassemble loaf.
Place in a paper lined basket or on a dinner plate. Cover with paper towel and microwave on Medium (50%) 1 minute. Rotate basket 1/2 turn.
Microwave until warm and cheese starts to melt, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes longer.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon and rolls together and broil burgers on the grill, preferably.
Top with cooked bacon slices and favorite condiments.

title: crab melt-aways
directions: Slice muffins in half.
Cut each half into fourths.
Arrange on 2 cookie sheets.
Mix ingredients well with electric beater (except crab meat).
Fold in crab meat; spread on pieces of muffins.
Broil until they puff up and get bubbly and a little brown.
Serve hot.
Makes 48.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onions; add drained beans and soup.
Put into casserole.
Mash potatoes; add milk, egg and seasoning.
Mound on hamburger.
Bake about 30 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon and nuts over apples.
Sprinkle cake mix over all.
Melt margarine and mix with milk; pour evenly over mix.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda. Heat liquids until very warm and add to dry mixture.
Beat well; add remaining flour to make it stiff.
Place in 2 greased and cornmeal sprinkled loaf pans.
Cover and let rise in a warm place 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and water; beat for 4 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake on second rack for 17 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Grease casserole; place 3 slices cut up bread on bottom.
Add half the sausage and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Beat eggs; add milk and mustard, then pour over all.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: baked cup custard
directions: Scald milk; remove from stove and add beaten eggs, sugar and salt.
Stir fast.
Pour into 10 custard cups, which have been set into a large pan of hot water.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from pan and cool.

title: blueberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; let stand to room temperature.
Add crushed pineapple and blueberry pie filling. Top with Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on bun.
Top with slice of sharp cheese and broil to melt cheese.
Top with other half of bun.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Brown meat with celery and onions.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Mix and spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: quick strawberry salad
directions: Mix together Jell-O powder and cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add fruit and nuts.
Ready to serve immediately or may be stored in refrigerator.

title: b.b.q. chicken sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over raw chicken and marinate. Best if grilled over an open-pit fire, but can be used for baked chicken with oven at 375.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and seasoning mix together.
Add additional hot pepper seasoning to taste.
Let stand at least 10 minutes for flavors to blend.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: marbled peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in a heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy reaches 234° on candy thermometer, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Marshmallow Creme and vanilla until well blended.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in ReaLemon.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: dumplings
directions: Cut the shortening into the dry ingredients, then add the milk.
Mix into ball and roll out on a floured board as thin as possible.
Cut in squares and drop in boiling broth.
You can also freeze them and cook at a later time.
They freeze well.

title: no fail asparagus souffle
directions: Stir (beat) well.
Spray bottom only of souffle (or casserole) dish.
Pour mixture into dish. Place dish in cake pan.
Fill cake pan with water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done, or knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
(Ovens vary, it takes approximately 1 1/2 hours.)

title: almond punch
directions: Combine and cook slowly.
After mixture is dissolved, boil for 2 minutes.
Makes 11 cups of syrup.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, one half cup of the sugar, butter and pecans together.
Press mixture very lightly into a 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, one cup sugar and whipped topping.
Spread on top of pretzel layer.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
When 75 percent congealed,
put on top of cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight before serving.

title: oatmeal carmelitas
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda and butter.
Blend well to form crumbs.
Press 1/2 of mixture into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Blend caramel sauce with 3 tablespoons flour.
Pour mixture over chips and nuts.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into bars.

title: apple slices
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, stir flour and salt.
Cut the butter in until crumbly, use a fork. Beat egg yolk and add enough milk to make 2/3 cup.
Stir into flour mixture; blend with fork.
Mix with hands.
If too sticky, add a little more flour.
Divide dough in half.
Make 2 balls.
Roll out dough thin; stretch with hands.
Don't grease pan.
Fill bottom of pan with 1/2 of dough rolled thin.
Spread 1 cup crushed cornflakes over crust.
Mix apple slices, sugar and cinnamon in a bowl; spread over cornflakes.
Place second 1/2 of dough, rolled out, on top of mixture as a top crust.
Use fork to seal edges.
Beat egg white until frothy and spread over crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool slightly.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Beat egg whites separate. Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese well. Add egg yolks and flour, a little at a time.
Add egg whites last.
Bake in tube or loaf pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn oven on after you set cake in.

title: creamy mashed potato
directions: Cook potatoes as directed on packages.
Then in mixing bowl, combine potatoes, cream cheese, and sour cream.
Blend together till smooth.
Place into baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 300 degrees.
Serve and enjoy.

title: braciolone(stuffed rolled beef)
directions: Spread steak with butter and layer onion over top.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients.
Roll up tightly and tie securely.
Brown in olive oil, turning often so as not to burn.
Lower heat; add wine.
Cover and cook slowly until fork-tender, about 1 hour. Braciolone may also be cooked in tomato sauce.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Blend margarine, flour and cream cheese together. Drop into greased miniature muffin pans, and press to form cups.
Mix eggs, brown sugar, vanilla, salt and nuts together and fill "up."
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: dream cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box.
When cake is baked and still hot, pour pineapple with juice over cake and cool.
Prepare pudding; omit 1/2 cup of milk to each box.
Mix the cream cheese with 1/2 cup milk; blend into pudding.
Spread over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients in double boiler (or heavy club aluminum pot), stirring occasionally until it thickens and drops from spoon in big blobs.
Remove from fire; add butter and vanilla.
Let cool completely, stirring occasionally.
Arrange alternate layers of pudding, bananas and vanilla wafers in a glass loaf pan.
Start and end with the pudding.
Beat egg whites until they start to stiffen.
Add cream of tartar and sugar, beating on high speed until forms stiff peaks.
Top pudding with meringue and brown lightly in oven under broiler.
Watch very carefully and do not overbrown.
Chill thoroughly until cold to set pudding.
Best served the same day.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in small amount of water for 10 minutes. Drain and mix soup, water chestnuts and pimentos.
Toss bread crumbs, slivered almonds and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: speedy chicken rolls with citrus-spice rice
directions: Prepare rice according to directions.
While rice cooks, place chicken breasts between 2 sheets of plastic wrap.
Using meat pounder or rolling pin, pound to 1/4-inch thickness.
Set aside.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Cook celery and onion together in a little water until tender.

title: holiday magic bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the margarine in an 8 x 11-inch Pyrex dish.
Add the graham cracker crumbs and press lightly. Layer the chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Then drizzle the condensed milk over all.
Bake 23 to 30 minutes.
If you want them thicker, use a smaller dish.

title: wacky tacky chicken thighs
directions: Brown chicken, arrange in casserole over raw rice.
Mix all soups together with 1 cup of water.
Pour over chicken and rice. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: treasured cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients for crust, press into spring-form pan and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix sugar and Kool-Aid in quart jar with water to make syrup. Refrigerate before adding to rest of punch.
Mix together syrup, sherbet and ginger ale.
Will make a mauve color punch.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Line a cookie sheet with foil. Spray foil with vegetable spray.
Place enough of the crumb mixture for one chicken in a plastic bag.
Shake pieces until thoroughly coated.
Place in pan, not touching.
Bake for 1 hour at 375° or until done.
Do not turn.
Discard the used crumb mix. Store unused mix in a tightly covered container.

title: italian beef
directions: Salt and pepper roasts.
Bake in a roaster, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Place sliced onions on the roast.
Cover and bake another 1 1/2 hours.
Separate beef and juice.
Cool overnight. Slice beef thin.
Add 1 1/2 cups water and bouillon to the juice.

title: lithuania noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook onions and garlic in butter.
Add noodles and remaining ingredients.
Turn into greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Pass grated Parmesan cheese.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix shortening and 1 cup sugar; beat well.
Add unbeaten egg; beat again.
Add molasses; mix well.
Mix dry ingredients and add, mixing well.
Form into small balls and dip in white sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until they crack (about 10 minutes).
Don't overbake.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Combine all ingredients; place in a greased dish. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cut into 1-inch squares. Serve warm.

title: easy pizza
directions: Spread sauce on muffins.
Sprinkle cheese over sauce.
Broil until cheese is melted.
Eat.
Yum yum!

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients well and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine all, except marshmallows, in mixing bowl.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with marshmallows.
Return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until marshmallows are browned.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Saute the onion in part of the melted butter.
Combine all ingredients to crock-pot.
Stir to mix.
Slow cook for 6 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and flour in margarine until golden brown.
Add meat mixed with salt and pepper.
Brown well.
Add mushrooms and soup.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and heat until all mixture is hot.
Serve on noodles or rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: party mix
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add garlic and seasoning salt.
Let simmer for 1 minute.
Pour over cereal and nuts.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let cool and serve.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring sugar, Carnation milk and margarine to boil over medium heat.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1 cup crunchy peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into long Pyrex dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Let cool and cut.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, put browned hamburger on bottom; sprinkle dry onion soup mix over hamburger.
Add vegetables and mushroom soup.
Put Tater Tots on top and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: aunt lola's chili sauce
directions: Put tomatoes and onions through a food chopper.
Add all other ingredients and boil for 2 hours or until thick, stirring frequently to prevent burning.
As soon as sauce is desired consistency, pour into sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: barbecue string beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion; add catsup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Drain beans and place in dish.
Pour sauce over beans.
Do not stir.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: applesauce pecan bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Mix together 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and next 5 ingredients.
Gradually add to first mixture until well mixed.
Stir in 1 cup nuts and the fruit.
Spread in a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix remaining nuts, cinnamon and brown sugar and spread evenly over batter and press in a little.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
To keep from overbrowning, spread foil over top last half an hour.
Turn out on side on a rack to cool.
Can be frozen.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Rinse peas under cold water in colander.
Drain well.
In bowl toss the macaroni with the peas.
Add the onion, celery, dill pickles, cheese, celery seeds, onion powder, garlic powder, and pepper. Toss and mix well.
Add mayo and a little celery salt. Toss well and taste.
Adjust seasonings to your taste.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients (salt, flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon); set aside.
Combine wet ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to wet and beat 2 minutes on high.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until raised area in center is moist, not wet.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together in bowl. Add oil, milk and egg; blend together until smooth.
Add cherries and mix together.
Pour into 9-inch prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until done when tested.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine all ingredients (except soup) in order listed.
Mix well.
Form into patties.
Roll lightly in flour and brown on both sides in butter.
Pour soup and 1 can water over meat patties. Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes, temperature about 250° in electric skillet.

title: "those" potatoes!
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake uncovered 1 hour at 350°. You can prepare this dish the night before.
Just cover and refrigerate before cooking.
If baking in a glass dish, let cold dish warm to room temperature before placing in a hot oven!

title: hot appetizer pie(dip for crackers)
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with milk.
Mix other ingredients with this except nuts.
Pat into an 8-inch pie dish. Spread walnuts over top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix brown sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Combine with ground beef and beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: caramel nuts
directions: Place each nut coated with batter onto greased pan.
Bake at 250° for 25 minutes.

title: all day deer stew
directions: Put deer meat in crock-pot.
Add all the other ingredients and cook 8 hours on low heat. This is good to put on at night and it's ready for your lunch the next day.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In medium saucepan, combine first 3 ingredients. Boil until it reaches the soft-ball stage. Add vanilla, baking soda and raw peanuts. Boil until it reaches the hard-boiled stage. Remove from heat and pour directly on greased (buttered) cookie sheets. Cool completely and crack the candy. Store in airtight container.

title: beef stew
directions: Dice all vegetables.
Place all ingredients in roaster.
Cover and bake at 250° for 4 1/2 hours.

title: pasta a la jimmy
directions: Boil pasta and drain.
Saute garlic in the olive oil until golden (be careful not to burn or scorch the garlic.)
Add chicken broth and parsley to the pan; stir briefly, then add cooked pasta to the pan and stir briefly.
Add freshly grated Parmesan or Romano cheese to taste and serve.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Cream the shortening until light, adding sugar. Add eggs, beating after each one.
Add molasses and coffee. Sift flour with spices and 1 teaspoon salt. Stir into creamed mixture. Add fruit and nuts.
Bake in a large pan at 275° for 3 hours. Will keep forever.

title: ice cream frosting
directions: Place in a bowl and mix well.
Add cooled custard to this mixture and beat until light and fluffy.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix the pudding and pineapple together well.
Add all but the Cool Whip and mix thoroughly.
Fold in the Cool Whip and refrigerate for 1 to 3 hours before serving.

title: classic reindeer snack
directions: In a big bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
Melt white chocolate and pour over dry mixture until they are mixed and covered in white chocolate.
Quickly pour out onto wax paper.
Let harden, then break into pieces.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Clean and peel potatoes.
Slice potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Then sprinkle with chives. Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer, until lightly browned, cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft inside.

title: graham cracker snack
directions: Boil oleo, brown sugar and pecans for 3 minutes; pour over graham crackers.
Put in oven just a few minutes.

title: steamed graham pudding
directions: Sift flour, whole wheat flour, sugar and soda together.
Mix remaining ingredients and blend with dry ingredients.
Steam steadily, but not hard for 2 hours.
Turn out of pan.
Serve hot or cold with any sauce desired.

title: fruit cake like my mama made
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, soda, salt and spice.
Cream butter, sugar and apples together.
Add to flour mixture; mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
It may not take that long.

title: garden ranch pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Arrange pizza dough side by side. Shape into a circle. Press seam to seal. Combine mayonnaise, season mix and garlic. Spread over crust. Top pizza with half of Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle broccoli, bell pepper, carrot and olives over pizza. Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese. Grate fresh Parmesan over pizza. Bake 18 to 22 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes, then serve. Enjoy!

title: denver style frittata
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch skillet over low heat.
Add mushrooms, green pepper and onion.
Saute over medium heat until tender (3 to 4 minutes).
If ham is water cured, microwave for 2 minutes; drain.
Add to skillet; saute 1 minute.
In medium bowl, combine eggs and water.
With electric mixer on high, beat until frothy. Pour into skillet.
Shake skillet vigorously to settle the eggs. Cook over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes.
Lift edge of set egg mixture with a metal spatula, tilt skillet gently toward opening to let uncooked egg to flow underneath.
Repeat at other edge points until there is only a small egg flow.
Cover skillet with 10-inch plate.
Invert plate, mixture, skillet slide mixture back into skillet.
Return to heat.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover.
When cheese is melted, slide frittata onto serving plate.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In blender, chop cranberries.
Drain pineapple; add to cranberries.
Mix in sugar.
Chill 1 to 2 hours in refrigerator. Add whipped cream and marshmallows.

title: cream cheese and olive spread
directions: Spread on party rye or thin white bread.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Place in a large bowl. Add all ingredients; mix well.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: mom's barbecue bean salad
directions: Toss lightly and marinate overnight.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon).
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Flatten with fork onto cookie sheet (as you would peanut butter cookies). Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Do not overbake.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ricotta cheese until blended.
Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add sugar and lemon juice to eggs. Gradually add egg mixture to cheese mixture.
Combine flour and cornstarch and stir into cheese mixture.
Add butter and vanilla. Mix well.
Add sour cream last.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 15 minutes, then at 375° for 40 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Leave cheesecake in oven for 1 hour without opening door.
Cool on rack.
Chill.

title: spinach stuffed flank steak
directions: In a well greased baking dish, lay the steak out flat, and salt and pepper the steak.
Layer the ham on one side of the steak.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread on top of ham. Roll steak jelly roll style and tie with cooking twine.
Brush with olive oil.
Bake at 375 degrees for 35 minutes.
Slice and serve with tomatoes.

title: tandy cake
directions: Combine all ingredients (except peanut butter and Hershey bars).
Pour in greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 300°.
While still hot, spread on thin layer of peanut butter. Refrigerate until cool.
Melt Hershey bars and spread over peanut butter.
Refrigerate.

title: pepper jelly
directions: You will also need sterilized jars, lids and rings.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, milk and vanilla.
Heat until well blended; pour into three 9-inch greased and floured pans.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add onion and green pepper to bacon grease and saute until onion is yellow.
Combine in baking dish with boiled rice, tomatoes, bacon (crumbled), salt and pepper.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top and bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes in a 400° oven.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: roadhouse chili
directions: Brown ground beef in a heavy skillet with onions, green peppers, garlic and butter; drain.
Add all of the other ingredients except the beans.
Simmer for 45 minutes, add more water as needed.
Add beans and simmer an additional 20 minutes. Spoon chili into bowls and serve.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except shoestring potatoes. Just before you are ready to serve, add 1 can of shoestring potatoes.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
Mix all ingredients together. Add nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Combine crust ingredients until crumbly.
Press down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve some for top.
(We double the crust.)

title: five minute fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly (time when mixture starts to "bubble" around edges of pan).
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, chocolate and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute (or until marshmallows melt).
Add nuts.
Pour into 8-inch square, buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayo and ranch dressing mix and set aside.
In large bowl layer the following in order - lettuce, cauliflower, mayonnaise mixture, cheese and bacon.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Toss before serving.

title: salsa verde
directions: Chop parsley, garlic and egg white very fine into bread.
Then crumble egg yolk and add to mixture.
Add salt and pepper and enough best quality olive oil until mixture is consistency of heavy cream.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix egg yolks and boiled rice; add mixture of corn meal, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add 1 pint of milk.
Melt butter in a baking dish and add mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix everything together well, then put one teaspoon of filling on each egg roll skin.
Wet edges to seal well.
Deep fry at 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, green pepper and onion in greased baking dish.
Season each layer with salt and pepper. Blend soup and milk.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: fresh strawberry jello pie
directions: First, bake pie shell and slice strawberries.
Cook cornstarch, sugar and water until clear.
Add jello and stir good.
Add strawberries and pour into shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: rice pudding
directions: Add all ingredients to saucepan.
Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice. Pour into bowl and cover.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl until creamy.
Blend in pourable fruit, 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour into greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: mother's slaw dressing
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Add sugar, vinegar, celery seed, dry mustard and salt.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Let cool.
Add desired amount to slaw.
Store remaining amount in refrigerator for later use.

title: cheese broccoli dip
directions: Heat garlic cheese, jalapeno cheese, mushroom soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Add broccoli.
Serve warm.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in bite-size chunks.
Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic bag add all ingredients.
Close bag tightly.
Shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty into shallow baking dish. Bake, stir occasionally for about 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can double and use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken and wine
directions: Saute sliced mushrooms and spread over chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in yogurt and lemon extract.
In small mixing bowl, stir together flour, poppy seed, salt, soda and baking powder.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Mix until combined.

title: fruits of the spirit salad
directions: Take a large heart and an average mind; toss with the listed ingredients lightly until well blended.
Add a dash of Faith the size of a grain of mustard seed.
Toss until well blended.
Yields 1 good Christian.
Repeat daily.

title: spinach and ricotta filling
directions: Cook chopped onion and butter until tender; add spinach and heat.
Combine the beaten egg, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese and nutmeg.
Add to spinach mixture.
Use to stuff pasta shells.
To cook casserole, in a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer sauce on bottom.
Lay shells in single layer.
Top with more sauce and Parmesan cheese.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: Combine bouillon cubes, water, vegetables and hash browns. Boil and then simmer 20 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup, milk and cheese.
Stir over low heat until the cheese is melted.

title: deluxe brownies(this is the ultimate brownie, if you like them rich and moist.)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine; mix with cocoa and oil. In separate bowl, beat sugar, vanilla and eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Beat in chocolate mixture on low speed.
Stir in nuts. Spread in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake just until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan (40 to 45 minutes).
Cool. Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: slumgullion
directions: Combine all ingredients in a skillet.
Cook until onion and bell pepper are cooked.
(Cheese slices on top are optional.)

title: marinated macaroni salad
directions: Combine the first five ingredients in a bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Pour over the shells and vegetables.
Mix together and let stand overnight.
Stir occasionally.

title: mexican buffet dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order in an 8 x 11-inch flat casserole or baking dish.
Make sure to spread the sour cream all the way to the edges to seal and keep the avocados green.
Refrigerate until serving.
Serve with crispy tortilla chips.

title: grandma's nutmeg cookies
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and nutmeg in a large bowl.
Stir into the dry ingredients the walnut meats, raisins, cut up dates, maraschino cherries or brickle bits.
(The brickle bits are quite new; look for them near the chocolate chips.)
You can use any of them or a combination, or anything else, or none.
I have never used chocolate chips, since I think they would seem like poor quality chocolate chip cookies!

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients into a large bowl.
Form a hole in center of dry mixture.
Beat together the next three ingredients. Pour into center of dry mixture.
Stir lightly.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 or 3 well-greased bread pans (1/2 full).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool 20 to 30 minutes before removing from pans. Cool completely on rack before cutting.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a saucepan and cook until thick.
Mix with regular mayonnaise about 1/2 and 1/2.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: onion sauerkraut relish
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add sugar. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture turns a light caramel color, about 10 minutes.
Add onion, sauerkraut and salt.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes, stirring frequently. Add vinegar and seed.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate for up to 3 weeks.
Good on hot dogs and brats.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and pie filling; ix until well blended. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool before frosting.
